column24: NOTES

Journalists today staged a street protest in the port city here as a lawmaker lodged a defamation suit against a journalist accusing him of tainting his image. The protest was organised by Bangladesh Federal Union of Journalists (BFUJ).
A local Awami League (AL) leader was hacked to death by assailants in Mirapara Bazar area under Bhadrabila union of Narail yesterday.
A suspected militant was killed in a gunfight with the police in Dhalhara-Binodpur road area in Sadar upazila in the early hours of today.
Two associate bodies of Awami League clashed on Thursday. An injured journalist died on the way to Dhaka on Friday afternoon.
On Thursday, there was a clash between supporters of  Awami League president Abdur Rahim (VP Rahim) and those of the party unit's Organising Secretary and Mayor Miru.
In protest of the assault on two ATN News journalists during January 26 hartal against Rampal power plant, journalists today formed a human chain in Karwan Bazar of Dhaka.

A man was killed and 10 others were injured in a clash between two groups of Awami League (AL) at Mathpara in Sadar upazila over establishing supremacy in the area on Friday morning. The two rival groups, equipped with arms, attacked each other, leaving Idris dead on the spot and 10 people injured.
A woman was killed in an attack over a land dispute with her neighbour at Singhadanga village in Gobindaganj upazila under Gaibandha on Friday.
Journalists and cultural activists in Jessore town formed a human chain and protest rally in front of Jessore Press Club on Saturday morning demanding arrest of the mayor.

Students laid siege to RUET's administrative building from Saturday afternoon to Sunday afternoon to protest against a new university rule that required students to complete 33 credits a year in order to be promoted to the next.

Jahangirnagar University Journalist Association (JUJA) formed a human chain on Sunday at JU Central Shaheed Minar premises. They werer potesting the murder of Abdul Hakim Shimul of Daily Samakal and demanding exemplary punishment to the killers immediately.

A Bangladeshi fisherman was shot dead and another injured as Myanmar Border Guard Police (BGP) opened fire on them while fishing in the Bay of Bengal near Teknaf upazila early Monday. A BGP team intruded into the Bangladesh water territory.
A former member of Kulkandi Union Parishad was killed by unidentified assailants at Baburchar village in Islampur upazila early Wednesday.
A man who sustained injuries in a clash over land at Purba Satjan village in Nautara union of Dimla upazila on Thursday, died at Rangpur Medical College Hosptal on Friday morning

Police clashed with BNP leaders and activists when they tried to gather near the Matsya Bhaban intersection in the city on Thursday morning. At least nine activists of BNP were injured during the clash.
At least 10 people, including a local journalist, were injured in a clash between two rival groups of Awami League in Sadarpur upazila on Thursday morning.
A person was killed and 40 people were injured in a clash between two groups at Shildai village of Brahmanpara upazila on Thursday.

Staffs of Sylhet Deputy Commissioner Office on Thursday attacked the officials of Anti-Corruption Commission (ACC) when they stormed their office to catch them with bribe money. Some persons were injured in the attack.

A man sustained bullet wounds and two women were injured in a clash between two groups of villagers over establishing supremacy at Mirza village in Hatiya upazila on Friday evening. Two groups, one led by incumbent chairman of Charkin Union Parishad Mahiuddin and the other by former chairman Mohiuddin Monir, had been at loggerheads over establishing dominance at the village.
A Bangladeshi national was shot dead by members of Indian Border Security Force (BSF) along Datbhanga border in Roumari upazila under Kurigram early Friday.
Ulashi union unit Bangladesh Chhatra League member was killed over a feud between two factions of the ruling party at Nabharan under Sharsha upazila in Jessore on February 11 night.
An activist of Bangladesh Chhatra League (BCL) was killed in a clash between its two rival groups in Riajuddin Bazar area of city on Saturday.
Eight people were injured in a clash between two factions of Bangladesh Chhatra League (BCL) at Chittagong University (CU) early Sunday.
Biplob's supporters blocked Jessore-Benapole road for one hour. Police rushed in and brought the situation under control.
A young man was shot during a clash between two factions of Awami League at the political office of MP Golam Dastagir in the city's Purana Paltan area on Monday.
A student of government city college was killed and another injured in a clash between two factions of students in the city's Reaz Uddin bazaar under Kotwali thana today.
An unidentified assailant was killed in a gunfight between his cohorts and police at Boikhor in the district town early Monday.
A unidentified assailant was killed and two children suffered bullet wounds in a gunfight between Bangladesh Army men and criminals in Lama upazila on Monday.
A suspected new JMB member was killed in a 'gunfight' with police at Patanja in Kahalu upazila early Tuesday. He was killed in a "gunfight" early Tuesday
A suspected militant was killed in a clash among two groups of people and police in Majherpara area of Maheshkhali upazila on Tuesday morning
A regional leader of the outlawed Purba Banglar Communist Party (PBCP) was killed in a gunfight with his rivals at Dhalarchar area in Bera upazila of Pabna district on Wednesday.

At least 22 people were injured, including 12 with bullets, in a clash between two rival groups over previous enmity in Jagannathpur upazila on Wednesday. As a sequel of the incident, the both groups, equipped with lethal weapons and firearms, attacked each other around.
A human chain was formed at the district Press Club premises today protesting the recent threat on two journalists and attacks on locals of Saltha upazila.

Mohiuddin's followers locked into a clash with Ifratul and his supporters on February 17, after Ifratul posted a comment on Facebook degrading ABM Mohiuddin Chowdhury, president of the city Awami League.

Thousands of people of all strata of Saltha and Nagarkandaupazila of Faridpur district Thursday staged a human chain in protest against propaganda lodged against Aimon Akbor Chowdhury, eminent politician, freedom fighter and son of the Deputy Leader of the House SyedaSajeda Chowdhury, at Nagarkanda.
Several hundred students gathered at the university main gate and blocked Sylhet-Sunamganj Highway, locked into a clash with locals and vandalised several shops in the area.
Local people set a bus afire following the death of a pedestrian in a road accident on Dhaka-Mymensingh highway in Masterbari area of Bhaluka upazila of Mymensingh on Tuesday night.

Transport workers have blocked five main routes of the district following a call for an indefinite transport strike in the district protesting bus driver Jamir Hossain's life sentence.  The District Bus and Truck Workers Union of Chuadanga started to enforced the strike from Wednesday following the announcement of the verdict.
At least 25 people, including 13 policemen, were injured in a clash between police and Jatiyatabadi Chhatra Dal (JCD) men in Kendua upazila headquarters on Friday noon.

A group of 60/70 villagers attacked the followers of 'Sureswar Majar' during their 'mahfil' in the area on Friday evening that led to a clash. A clash ensued between these two groups and the police in Tumchar area of Lakshmipur.
The government's plan to shift the Myanmar refugees from Cox's Bazar has triggered protests in Noakhali with residents demonstrating against it.

Hundreds of Saat Tola slum dwellers of Mohakhali on Sunday staged a demonstration in front of Dhaka Water and Sewerage Authority (WASA)'s Zonal Office Mods Zone 5. They were demanding immediate solution to the ongoing water crisis in the slum area.
A local Awami League activist was found dead near a fishing enclosure at Pabla area in Khulna on Monday.
Bangladesh Federal Union of Journalists (BFUJ) today staged a rally and formed human chain in front of Jatiya Press Club (JPC) here. They were demanding for constituting the 9th wage board.
Garment workers protested steadily for one week at Phnom Penh Tower, claiming a retail giant was complicit in witholding workers' salaries.
More than 400 fishing families in four communities in Kampot province protested to demand authorities prevent illegal fishing by Vietnamese fishermen in Cambodian waters.
Garment workers protested steadily for one week at Phnom Penh Tower, claiming a retail giant was complicit in witholding workers' salaries.
Garment workers protested steadily for one week at Phnom Penh Tower, claiming a retail giant was complicit in witholding workers' salaries.
Garment workers protested steadily for one week at Phnom Penh Tower, claiming a retail giant was complicit in witholding workers' salaries.

Workers from a garment factory protested outside the factory in Kampong Speu province's Chbar Mon town after their employer vanished without paying a month of their salaries. About 300 workers joined the protest.
Garment workers protested steadily for one week at Phnom Penh Tower, claiming a retail giant was complicit in witholding workers' salaries.

About 40 villagers from Phnom Penh gathered at the district governor's house, requesting that he help them obtain compensation for land taken for a government project to build a satellite city on a peninsula.
Garment workers protested steadily for one week at Phnom Penh Tower, claiming a retail giant was complicit in witholding workers' salaries.
Garment workers protested steadily for one week at Phnom Penh Tower, claiming a retail giant was complicit in witholding workers' salaries.
Eight police personnel were killed and five injured in a landmine blast triggered by suspected Maoists in Odisha's Koraput district on Wednesday.
A jawan of 2nd JK Light Infantry was injured in a bomb blast at Nachou, Bishenpur district last night.

A mob of nearly 200 people were arrested for resorting to road blockade and burning tires after police took objection to pictures of religious figures put up at the welcome arch of Padma Nagar in Bhiwandi.

Since January 16, the All India Kisan Sabha has been holding protests in different parts of the state seeking that the government roll back the hike and offer farmers and other consumers of electricity relief. Large numbers of farmers gathered in Churu.

Since January 16, the All India Kisan Sabha has been holding protests in different parts of the state seeking that the government roll back the hike and offer farmers and other consumers of electricity relief. Large numbers of farmers gathered in Hanumangarh.

Since January 16, the All India Kisan Sabha has been holding protests in different parts of the state seeking that the government roll back the hike and offer farmers and other consumers of electricity relief.

Since January 16, the All India Kisan Sabha has been holding protests in different parts of the state seeking that the government roll back the hike and offer farmers and other consumers of electricity relief. Large numbers of farmers gathered in Jhunjunu.

Five members of a Badaun-based family attempted self immolation in front of Vidhan Bhawan in Lucknow on Wednesday, alleging police inaction against a local politician's aide who allegedly abducted their minor daughter nearly five months ago. Police deployed at Vidhan Bhawan foiled their suicide bid.

Activists of the Shree Hindu Takhat burnt the effigy of Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) supremo Arvind Kejriwal near the city railway station in Ludhiana on Wednesday, alleging that Kejriwal and his leaders were aligned with the Khalistani activists.

Local leaders and workers of the Aam Aadmi Party staged a dharna outside the police station in Maur town on Wednesday, demanding strict action against those behind the car blast near a rally of a Congress candidate at Maur Mandi the day before. They raised slogans against the SAD-BJP ruling alliance for allegedly pressuring the Police Department and administration.

Since January 16, the All India Kisan Sabha has been holding protests in different parts of the state seeking that the government roll back the hike and offer farmers and other consumers of electricity relief. Large numbers of farmers gathered in Nagaur.

Union minister Vijay Goel on Wednesday launched his 'Delhi Bachao' campaign along with activists of NGOs and resident welfare association members, protesting the "pathetic" condition of the city under the alleged "misgovernance" of the AAP government.

Over 500 members of the Indian Medical Association, Punjab, held a protest in Patiala on Wednesday to oppose some amendments to the Indian Medical Council Act through the Medical Council of India by the Ministry of Health and Family Welfare.

Protesting workers called off their protest which they had been staging since January 30 this year on Wednesday after the intervention of the officials of the district administration and ONGC authorities. The contractual workers of ONGC under the banner of Deprived Contractual Workers' Union have set a 15-day timeline for the authorities of ONGC Cachar Forward Base to respond to their demands for regularisation of jobs. [Day 3]

Several people were injured when police used force to disperse a group of BJP party activists who were marching towards the Law Academy in Thiruvananthapuram as part of their agitation against Academy Principal Dr Lakshmi Nair. Party workers gathered in large number at Peeroorkada junction where police resorted to lathicharge, burst teargas shells and used water canons to disperse the violent crowd which pelted stones at the police.

Since January 16, the All India Kisan Sabha has been holding protests in different parts of the state seeking that the government roll back the hike and offer farmers and other consumers of electricity relief. Large numbers of farmers gathered in Tonk.
Suspected Maoists attacked the camp office of a road construction firm and set on fire two vehicles near Barachatti town in Bihar's Gaya district, about 110 km south of Patna, on Wednesday night.

Three personnel of a private company sustained minor injuries when suspected Maoists exploded a crude bomb in the Amrapali Open Cast Project of Central Coalfields Limited (CCL) under Tandwa police station of area Jharkhand's Chatra district. The incident occurred late Wednesday night.
Medical students of JLN Medical College in Ajmer staged a protest against the National Exit Test (NEXT) on Thursday.
An anti-liquor padayatra was organised from Basavakalyana to Bengaluru by the Madya Nishedha Andolana Karnataka, as part of a state-wide agitation.

Police used water cannons to disperse protesting Congress workers as they marched towards the Char Imli bungalow of Madhya Pradesh home minister Bhupendra Singh in Bhopal. More than a dozen party workers, including the state Youth Congress president Kunal Choudhry were arrested. The protest was organised against the increasing incidents of alleged misbehaviour by BJP leaders.
The Odisha Nursing Employees' Association sat on adharna in front of the hospital superintendent's office today to press for their demands.
The road to Kohima from Dimapur, National Highway 39, remained blocked from 4th Mile area here since last night with protesters felling trees and placing boulders on it.
In Dimapur, a house on a plot of land at Diphupar here belonging to the Chief Minister, was set afire last night.

One person was injured and over a dozen parked vehicles damaged when two groups of men clashed with each other during the immersion of a Saraswati idols in the Yamuna in East Delhi's Geeta Colony on Thursday evening.
Yesterday non-locals students of the IIIT, Manipur protested inside the campus located at Mantripukhri, on the outskirts of Imphal, after the authority failed to supply chapatti to the non-locals.
A clash between the muslims of Kshetrigao Awang Leikai and the state police force took place today.

A clash broke out between Congress workers outside a club in Juhu, where Singh Hooda, the former Haryana chief minister, was meeting with senior party leaders. During the clashes, Arif Sayyad, a minority cell leader was beaten up when he said he would support Mumbai Congress chief Sanjay Nirupam.

column23: Asian News International (ANI); Indian Express; The Telegraph (India)
column24: Violence erupted across Nagaland's capital Kohima on Thursday over women reservation in Urban local bodies polls. Thousands of protesters targeted several government offices and even set on fire the municipal office.

Pre-poll clashes broke out today in Wangkhem and Heirok Assembly constituencies of Thoubal district. A clash reportedly took place at Lourembam village in Heirok constituency, involving workers of Manipur Peoples' Party. Police controlled the people by firing tear gas shells. A woman was injured.

Residents gathered in large numbers at the place where the bomb blast had taken place on January 31 and blocked the path of the Bathinda SSP Swapan Sharma’s vehicle in Maur Mandi on Thursday to protest against  the lack of medical facilities and fire brigade.

Akali supporter Tajinder Singh and Congress’ Ranjodh Singh along with their supporters attacked each other over allegations that Akali leaders were luring voters with liquor in Naushera Pannua in Tarn Taran district. Both men were admitted to a local hospital.
Over 200 students of Jawaharlal Nehru University held a protest near Shastri Bhawan in Central Delhi on Thursday to demand a rollback of the University Grants Commission's May 5, 2016, notification.

column9: INTUC: Indian National Trade Union Congress
column24: Employees of JCT Mills, belonging to INTUC and led by union president Om Parkash, held a demonstration and raised slogans against the ESI administration in Phagwara for the alleged negligence in work which lead to the death of a labourer of the JCT Mill on Wednesday.

Women in Raichur carried out an anti-liquor protest from Gandhi Circle to the excise department office, asking the department officials to hand over the portrait of Mahatma Gandhi. The protest was organised by the Madya Nishedha Andolana Karnataka.

Protesting workers called off their protest which they had been staging since January 30 this year on Wednesday after the intervention of the officials of the district administration and ONGC authorities. The contractual workers of ONGC under the banner of Deprived Contractual Workers' Union have set a 15-day timeline for the authorities of ONGC Cachar Forward Base to respond to their demands for regularisation of jobs. [Day 4]

Female students from the Holy Angels Convent in Thiruvananthapuram took to the streets after learning that there would be a new retail outlet of the state-owned Beverages Corporation (Bevco) near their school. This followed the recent directive of the Supreme Court that there should be no liquor outlets on national and state highways.

Pre-poll clashes broke out today in Wangkhem and Heirok Assembly constituencies of Thoubal district. Workers of a candidate of Wangkhem constituency interrupted the flag hoisting function held at the residence of one Congress worker Yumnam Umakanta at Kiyam Siphai, Thoubal. Police brought the situation under control by firing tear gas shells.

On February 2, members of Wangkhem Block Mahila Congress Committee were allegedly assaulted by workers of Yumnam Nabachandra of Indian National Congress who is an intending candidate of the coming 2017 assembly election in the 32-Wangkhem assembly constitution.
Following an attack on AAP workers by SAD supporters on February 2, AAP activists  staged a protest in front of the Zirakpur police station, demanding action against the accused.

Akali leader Gurwinderpal Singh, former sarpanch of Khadoor Sahib village and former chairman of the Market Committee, was shot at by unidentified persons late on Thursday evening near Beharipur village in Tarn Taran district. He escaped unhurt.

Akali supporters allegedly attacked and assaulted two Congress workers with sharp-edged weapons at Boparai village in Tarn Taran district on Thursday as the victims had opposed distribution of liquor and cash by SAD leaders at the village. The two victims were admitted to a private hospital.

A group of Maoists killed a 25-year-old youth who wanted to join the police force, and allegedly thrashed several others at Burdikarka village in Dantewada district, Chhattisgarh, after locals refused to support their activities.

column8: CPI(M): Communist Party of India (Marxist) Militia
column24: A BJP worker died after he was attacked at a temple near Kadakkal town in Kollam district, Kerala, by 5 CPI(M) cadres. They were later arrested.

CPI (Maoists) gunned down two persons including one former cadre member of rival Tritiya Sammelan Prastuti Committee. The incident took place during a cultural programme under Kunda police station of Chatra district on Thursday night.

An AAP worker was allegedly attacked and by Congress workers with wooden sticks in Nangal Kalan village of Mansa district on Thursday night following an objection over distribution of liquor in the village. The victim was hospitalised in Mansa Civil Hospital.
On 2 February, an MLA assaulted a boy, convicting him to be involved in a clash before the election. The incident took place at Tangjeng under Thoubal police station.
SAD workers allegedly attacked AAP workers and their families with swords and rods at Nabha locality of Zirakpur town on February 2. Some of the victims had to be submitted to hospital for treatment.
SAD and Congress workers, both armed with sharp-edged weapons, clashed in Khanauri village of Sangrur district on Friday. The Congress office and three vehicles were reportedly damaged.
A police constable was killed and another injured in an exchange of fire with naxals near Bhave village, Rajnandgaon district in Chhatisgarh. The maoists escaped into the jungle soon after.

Following the death of a patient, a mob of 45 persons started rioting at the VS Hospital in Paldi late on Friday. The mob not only indulged in vandalism but also reportedly entered into a violent scuffle with the bouncers at the hospital, who were called in to pacify them. One of the bouncers sustained injuries in his arm and had to be admitted.

MBBS students of the MKCG Medical College Hospital on Wednesday joined the nationwide stir, called by the Indian Medical Association (IMA), against the Centre's proposal of an exit test (National Exit Test or NEXT) for MBBS graduates to qualify for medical practice. Hundreds of students moved in a rally in the college campus.
Members of the Chandigarh UT Subordinate Service Federation held a protest outside the UT Secretariat in Sector 9, Chandigarh, on Friday, against recent inter-departmental transfers.
Four people were injured in a poll-related clash between SAD and Congress activists at Chhapianwali village in Lambi on Friday night.
Members of Nikhil Bishnupriya Manipuri Yuva Parishad yesterday staged a sit-in demonstration at Dispur Last Gate. They were pressing for various longstanding demands concerning the community.

State Congress chief Capt Amarinder Singh and AAP’s Jarnail Singh along with their supporters staged a protest against SAD halqa chief Gurbakhshish Singh ‘Vicky’  Middukhera in Lambi’s Hakkuwala village on Friday for allegedly distributing money to voters.

Villagers vandalised the vehicle of SAD halqa chief Gurbakhshish Singh ‘Vicky’ Middukhera and his son Gurlal Singh at Hakkuwala village in Lambi constituency on Friday. The SAD men allegedly had come to the village to distribute money to voters.

Students and workers of the ABVP shouted slogans and forcibly shut the Jai Narayan Vyas University in Jodhpur on Friday, to protest the 'anti-national' address by a professor of Jawaharlal Nehru University, Nivedita Menon.
On Friday, three members of the Association for Protection of Democratic Rights (APDR) were attacked while on their way to court. The group has blamed TMC workers for the attack.
SAD and Congress workers clashed in Kotbhai village in Gidderbaha Assembly segment on Friday.
BJP MPs sat on a dharna outside the parliament (assumed in Lucknow) on Friday to protest the poor law and order situation in Uttar Pradesh state under the Samajwadi Party (SP) government.

A BJP candidate from Ludhiana West Kamal Chatly and his supporters manhandled Congress workers and ransacked the office Congress candidate Bharat Bhushan Ashu at BRS Nagar locality in Ludhiana city on Friday, alleging that the latter had stored liquor which was to be distributed to voters.

Minor poll-related skirmishes and scuffles between party workers were recorded in Maiserkhana constituency on Friday night as supporters accused each other of trying to lure voters by distributing liquor and cash among voters.

column9: AIJASS: All India Jat Aarakshan Sangharsh Samiti
column24: Jat community members living in Delhi, under the banner of All India Jat Aarakshan Sangharsh Samiti, staged a protest in Mahipalpur area of Delhi on February 5, demanding quota for Jats in central government jobs among others.

The Trinamool Congress (TMC) on Friday staged a protest near Mahatma Gandhi's statue on the Parliament premises in New Delhi, against the BJP-led government at the Centre over demonetisation and the arrest of senior party member Sudip Bandyopadhyay in connection with the chit-fund scam.

Protesting workers called off their protest which they had been staging since January 30 this year on Wednesday after the intervention of the officials of the district administration and ONGC authorities. The contractual workers of ONGC under the banner of Deprived Contractual Workers' Union have set a 15-day timeline for the authorities of ONGC Cachar Forward Base to respond to their demands for regularisation of jobs. [Day 5]

Two assailants on a motorcycle opened fire at the Agricultural Produce Market Committee (APMC) president K Srinivas near Kogilu Junction on airport road in Bengaluru, injuring him and his driver. The two were taken to hospital for treatment and survived. The motive behind the attack is unknown.

BSP candidate from Khanna — Shashi Vardhan — was  allegedly attacked by some persons, including PA of Congress candidate, at Amloh Chowk in Khanna on Friday when he tried to stop Congress workers from campaigning. Vardhan was admitted to a hospital for treatment.
Maoists gunned down a civilian in Malkangiri district, over 600 km from Bhubaneswar, in the early hours of Friday.

Aam Aadmi Party (AAP)’s Rampura youth coordinator, Robby Brar, was attacked and shot in the thigh by SAD’s former market committee chairman Rocky Kansal in the early hours on Friday after objecting to the distribution of illicit liquor among the voters by SAD workers. Brar has been admitted to Adesh Hospital in Bathinda for surgery.

Following a deadly accident in Ahmedabad on Friday night, AAP members and the victims' relatives staged a protest at the spot on Saturday, demanding justice from the authorities. With numbers swelling and things turning chaotic, police detained 10 persons.

North 24 Parganas' Amdanga turned violent on Saturday following protest over prolonged power cuts. At least five policemen were injured during a clash with a protesters. The cops were trying to lift a road blockade on NH-34.
Several BJP workers thrashed a Congress worker over a poll-related argument at Anand Avenue near the Faizpura area in the Amritsar North constituency on Saturday.
Five persons assaulted and slapped an  supporter of Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) near the residence of party candidate Gurmeet Singh Meet Hayer in Barnal on Saturday after polling had ended.
A poll-related clash between SAD city president Sudhir Bansal and Congress supporters was reported outside the polling station on Railway road in Bathinda on Saturday.

SAD workers raised objection and staged protest at booth number 196 at Tarun Public School near Sukhpeer road in Bathinda on Saturday, alleging that Congress worker Chamkaur Mann had entered the polling booth after 5 pm when doors were closed.

Supporters of former SAD sarpanch Dalip Singh and Congress’ existing sarpanch Satta Singh hurled stones at each other after a poll-related dispute outside a polling booth at Bhindi Saida village in the Rajasansi constituency in Amritsar on Saturday. Paramilitary forces used mild force to disperse them. Two persons were reportedly injured in the incident.
A minor poll-related clash took place between Congress and BJP workers at Samrala village in Bhoa Assembly segment in Pathankot district on Saturday.

Relatives of a youth killed in broad daylight by a dozen assailants on Friday, blocked traffic on the Kaithal-Patiala road for five hours on Saturday by placing the body of the deceased in the middle of the Kaithal-Patiala road, near the Udham Singh Chowk in Cheeka, Kaithal, demanding the arrest of the accused.
A minor poll-related clash between workers of political parties was reported from Dera Baba Nanak on Saturday.
A minor poll-related clash between workers of political parties was reported from Dhuri on Saturday.

Volunteers of the Nagaland Tribes Action Committee (NTAC) and Joint Coordination Committee (JCC) blocked entry to government offices and prevented government vehicles from plying in Kohima and Dimapur on Saturday.
A minor poll-related clash took place between a local SAD and Congress leader in Ferozepur (Rural) constituency on Saturday.
An incidents of poll-related firing was reported from Ferozepur on Saturday.
A minor poll-related clash between workers of political parties was reported from Gur Har Sahai on Saturday.

The family of a man who died allegedly due to a heart attack after he cast his vote at Bashirpura locality in Jalandhar city on Saturday, staged a protest at the polling booth, not allowing the police to shift the body to the Civil Hospital for a post-mortem.
A minor poll-related clash took place between Congress and BJP workers at Preet Nagar locality of Jalandhar city on Saturday.
AAP and Congress workers had a poll-related clash at Kalanaur, near Batala, on Saturday, in which police had to use mild force to diffuse the situation.
SAD activist Kulwinder Singh sustained head injury in a poll-related clash with Congress activists at Killianwali village in Lambi on Saturday.

Volunteers of the Nagaland Tribes Action Committee (NTAC) and Joint Coordination Committee (JCC) blocked entry to government offices and prevented government vehicles from plying in Kohima and Dimapur on Saturday.

A poll-related incident of violence between Congress and Akali supporters was reported from Kotshamir in Bathinda on Saturday, over allegations regarding distribution of money during polling. The police intervened to bring the situation under control.
A minor poll-related clash took place between SAD and AAP workers at Kotkapura in Faridkot district on Saturday.
A minor poll-related clash between workers of political parties was reported from Lehragaga on Saturday.

A few bike-borne supporters of the SAD candidate from Ludhiana West Hira Singh Gabria allegedly attacked and hurled stones at the car of Lok Insaaf Party (LIP) candidate from the same constituency at Daba locality of Ludhiana on Saturday. No one was injured in the incident.
Following an attack on a Lok Insaaf Party (LIP) candidate, LIP supporters ransacked the office of SAD candidate Singh Gabria located on the Daba road in Ludhiana on Saturday.
AAP and SAD workers clashed in Maiserkhana on Saturday over the issue of taking an elderly voter to the polling booth.

SAD workers allegedly manhandled the officiating granthi of the local gurdwara at Jwaharke village in Mansa on Saturday morning after the latter urged villagers to keep the desecration incidents in mind and the fact that no accused had been arrested in any of these cases.

Supporters of Aam Aadmi Party candidate Jagdev Singh Kamalu and supporters of Shiromani Akali Dal candidate Janmeja Singh Sekhon clashed during the last hour of polling at Maur on Saturday. The police intervened to bring the situation under control.

A Mohali Municipal Corporation councillor Sahibe Anand (BJP) was allegedly thrashed by district's sitting MLA Balbir Singh's brother, his son and other accused owing alliance to the Congress in an incident of poll-related violence on Saturday.

A minor poll-related clash took place between Congress and Akali Dal workers in Gandhi Nagar area of Rampura on Saturday after the former objected to the alleged distribution of money and liquor among the voters by the latter.
Six persons were injured during a poll-related clash between Congress and SAD supporters at Ropowali village in Fatehgarh Churian constituency on Saturday.

Protesting workers called off their protest which they had been staging since January 30 this year on Wednesday after the intervention of the officials of the district administration and ONGC authorities. The contractual workers of ONGC under the banner of Deprived Contractual Workers' Union have set a 15-day timeline for the authorities of ONGC Cachar Forward Base to respond to their demands for regularisation of jobs. [Day 6]

Today, during his dharna, Simdega Chamber of Commerce and Industry president Motilal Agrawal was accompanied by several others, including senior BJP leaders Om Prakash Sahu and Shyamlal Sharma, Congressman Kaushal Rohilla, JMM leader Louise Kujur and INTUC leader Rajesh Kumar Singh.

Following an attack on a local Congress councillor by SAD workers on Saturday evening, Congress workers and supporters, led by Kuljeet Singh Nagra, blocked the Railway Road in Sirhind to protest the alleged assault.
Two persons were injured in a poll-related clash which took place between AAP and Congress workers at Sultanpur village in Sangrur district on Saturday.
A minor poll-related clash between workers of political parties was reported from Taran  on Saturday.
A minor poll-related clash took place in Mallanwala in Zira on Saturday.
An incidents of poll-related firing was reported from Lohgarh locality of Zirakpur town on Saturday.

Akali candidate from Fatehgarh Sahib Didar Singh Bhatti’ younger son Jashanpreet Singh and other supporters attacked Congress councillor Gulshan Rai Bobby, his brother Ashok Kumar and his wife Meena Kumari in their house in Humayunpur area under the Sirhind Municipal Council after the polling came to an end on Saturday evening.

Following the death of the chief controller at the North Central Railway (NCR), the control staff of Jhansi division put the body of their colleague outside the Jhansi control office and staged a demonstration on Thursday, demanding compensation for the deceased's family.

More than 1,000 college students today staged a protest demonstration in front of Jorhat Sadar Police Station here. They were demanding the arrest and punishment of a gang of eve-teasers allegedly accused of molesting a degree-level girl student of a prestigious college in the city.
BJP workers of Karsog area staged a protest against state government and burnt an effigy of CM Virbhadra Singh in front of Sub Divisional Magistrate office at Karsog in Mandi on Thursday.

Residents of Jitwal Kalan village blocked  the Sangrur-Malerkotla road in front of the police complex in Malerkotla town, alleging that village youth Bikramjit Singh Bobby who was shot during cross-firing between the police and criminals on Wednesday night had been murdered in cold blood by the police.

Residents of lower Assam's Darrang district took out a rally, as Rajbongshi hails from Darrang. Members of the All Assam Koibarta Students' Union were seen standing in front of Sivasagar Natya Mandir where the delegates' meeting was held.

Members of the Jawaharlal Nehru University Students Union (JNUSU) sat on a dharna at the administrative building on campus on Thursday, demanding revocation of the May 5 2016 regulations on the new admission process. Students have also been sitting on a hunger strike since January 31. Day 1
Congress MPs staged protests in both Houses of Parliament on Thursday, demanding Modi’s apology for his remarks against Manmohan Singh in the Rajya Sabha.
Residents of the nearby areas led by Sarabjeet Ukhla (AAP) staged a protest against the dumping of garbage close to various educational institutions in Patiala city. Day 2
A large number of residents staged a protest against the poor law and order situation in Rampura Mandi in Rampura Phul city on Thursday.
Members of the Safai Mazdoor Union took out a protest march in Rampura Phul on Thursday, demanding the arrest of those accused of killing the 58-year-old safai sewak.
Today, around 100 teachers demonstrated in front of the Siliguri DI office against the alleged discrimination by the government.

Residents of lower Assam's Darrang district took out a rally. However, members of the All Assam Koibarta Students' Union were seen protesting in front of Sivasagar Natya Mandir where the delegates' meeting was held.
Members of the State Government Employees Federation locked the office of Executive Engineer (XEN) of the Public Health Department in Sriganganagar on Thursday, in support of their demands.

A group of parents staged a protest at Gajera Vidhyabhavan in Katargam locality of Surat city, alleging molestation of a class I girl by a school van driver. The parents demanded action against the driver.
Hundreds of activists from both Karnataka and Kerala continued to protest against the toll collection in Thalapady. Police were there to maintain order, but no clashes occurred.

The three-day dharna programme staged by the civic body employees that began on February 8 last in Tinsukia concluded today. Beside the sit-in dharna, the members of the Tinsukia branch of All Assam Municipal Employees' Union organised a rally February 8. [Day 2]

Tinsukia District Committee of Krishak Mukti Sangram Samitee (KMSS) staged a sit-in dharna in front of the Deputy Commissioner's office complex here on Thursday demanding roll back of recent hike in the land revenues of all kinds in the State. Protesters alleged that the hike in the revenues would hamper the people, especially the rural people and the farmers.

column9: AIJASS: All India Jat Aarakshan Sangharsh Samiti
column24: Protesters from All India Jat Aarakshan Sangharsh Samiti took out a protest march towards the sports stadium at Umrakheri village near the Panipat-Shamli road on Thursday, demanding quota for Jats in central government jobs among others. Day 12

A group of more than 20 youths armed with sharp-edged weapons attacked three others in emergency ward of the Bhakra Beas Management Board Hospital in Nangal, injuring them seriously, on Thursday. The assailants also vandalised the hospital.
Two boys were killed when two groups clashed over a property dispute at Ghosipur village of Meerut's Kharkora area on Friday evening.
A Maoist was killed in an encounter with security personnel in Chattisgarh's Bilaspur district.
A Naxal was killed during an encounter with police (Central Reserve Police Force and the District Police Force) near Chilkapalli village in Chhattisgarh's Bijapur district.
After a fatal accident at Bhikhanpur village under Ahiyapur police station area, locals held violent protests and put up road blockade on the national highway. Police were attacked with stones.

Bilaspur residents protested against the bail granted to youths who attacked three teenagers in Diyara on Friday. They raised slogans against Bilaspur MLA Bambher Thakur whose son is one of the accused.
The Jat Nyay Samiti staged a dharna at Daultabad village in Gurugram on Friday.

A group of over 50 women launched an indefinite protest outside a wine and beer shop under Delhi Tourism and Transport Development Corporation (DTTDC), demanding that it be shut down as it stands barely 30 metres from a government school in southwest Delhi's Dwarka.

Hundreds of drivers in Hyderabad took to the streets to protest against Ola and Uber. The drivers, part of the Telangana Cab Drivers and Owners Association, begged at a traffic signal in a semi-nude condition to highlight their plight.

State-wide protest demanding resignation of Chief Minister T.R. Zeliang continued. The protesters are not allowing the functioning of government offices and preventing government vehicles to ply on the roads.

Following the emerging of a video showing a Congress worker from Bhai Rupa village being forced to strip by police men, Congress workers on Friday took out a protest march at Mehraj village in Bathinda district, demanding that the police register a case against SAD leaders on whose pressure cops forced the victim to strip.

Members of the Jawaharlal Nehru University Students Union (JNUSU) sat on a dharna at the administrative building on campus on Friday, demanding revocation of the May 5 2016 regulations on the new admission process. Later in the day, the JNU Teachers' Association (JNUTA) along with students held a protest march towards the Parliament. Day 2

Cab drivers staged a protest against mobile-based cab aggregators Ola and Uber at Jantar Mantar in New Delhi on Friday, raising various demands, including non-lowering of rates, life insurance for drivers and non-preference for taxis owned by the firms. Cabs owned by the firms were stopped by protesters across the city and passengers forced out of the vehicles by protesting drivers. Day 1
Residents of the nearby areas led by Sarabjeet Ukhla (AAP) staged a protest against the dumping of garbage close to various educational institutions in Patiala city. Day 3

Led by former Congress minister Joginder Singh Mann, party workers staged a protest in front of the office of SP in Phagwara on Friday, demanding action against the two SHOs  who had raided the house of Congress supporter Vivek Chadha who has been accused of attempting to molest a BJP councillor and attacking her husband.
Fishermen in Puducherry held a demonstration to protest the delay in the dredging of the estuary of the fishing harbour.

Around 150 students and their parents of Government Girls/Boys Senior Secondary School, Shahbad Dairy in Rohini locality of New Delhi, blocked the Bawana Road on Friday to protest against "constant threat and harassments" that the students were being subjected to.

Inhabitants of coastal villages like Budia, Jiav, Dipli and others staged a dharna near MTB College in Surat city on Friday, demanding the closure of an industrial unit located about 200m from Budia village. The dharna was staged under the banner of Kantha Vibhag Yuva Koli Samaj Parivartan Trust.
Students of Samras Hostel, on the Veer Narmad South Gujarat University (VNSGU) campus in Surat, staged  a dharna on Friday to protest the lack of basic amenities at the hostel.

The three-day dharna programme staged by the civic body employees that began on February 8 last in Tinsukia concluded today. Beside the sit-in dharna, the members of the Tinsukia branch of All Assam Municipal Employees' Union organised a rally February 8. [Day 3]

Tinsukia district committee of All Assam Hindu Students' Union (AAHSU) submitted a memorandum and protested, demanding that encroachers on footpaths of Tinsukia town should be evicted so that the pedestrians can make hassle-free movements.

Manpreet Kaur Dolly, daughter of AAP candidate Bibi Sarabjit Kaur, along with party workers, on Friday took out a procession in town and held a protest in front of the Zirakpur police station, accusing cops of inaction against eight people, who allegedly attacked party workers on February 2 night.
Suspected militants gunned down a farmer couple in Assam's Udalguri district last night.

In an incident of Hindu-Muslim violence, a group of armed Muslim men from Pedda village in Bijnor district, attacked and killed a Jat youth and critically injured his father at Nayagon village in the same district on Friday.
Some people opened fire on each other in a village in Kithaur area on Saturday over poll-related dispute between the Samajwadi Party (SP) and Bahujan Samaj Party (BSP).
Students protested against “arbitrary” fee hikes by Panjab University for BA and MA courses in Abohar on Saturday.
Minor poll-related clashes were recorded in Aligarh during the first of seven phases of the Assembly Elections in Uttar Pradesh on Saturday.

Members of different communities clashed in Baghu colony in Baghpat on Saturday city when one side tried to stop the other from casting their votes. In the clash, ten persons were injured and admitted to hospital.
A poll-related clash was reported in Looyan village under Badaut area of Baghpat district on Saturday, after Rashtriya Lok Dal (RLD) workers obstructed Dalit voters from casting their vote.
Over a thousand citizens formed a human chain in Bengaluru in a protest to save trees along the Jayamahal road, which were scheduled to be cut for infrastructure projects.

Activists of the Bengali students group federation today burnt an effigy of chief minister Sarbananda Sonowal in Bijni protesting against the government's failure to ensure citizenship for Hindu Bengali migrants.
On Saturday, around 200 people staged a protest on the Bijnor main road for five hours demanding justice and compensation for the family of Vishal who was killed the day before.
Minor poll-related clashes were recorded in Etah during the first of seven phases of the Assembly Elections in Uttar Pradesh on Saturday.
Residents of Ansal's Sushant Lok-I in Gurgaon on Saturday staged a protest against civic apathy and the failure of agencies to build roads and boost power supply to the area.

Around 200 cab drivers from Hyderabad organised a 'Vanta Varpu' programme (cooking on roads) to protest against taxi aggregators. Police took 21 cab drivers into custody. The protest, held near Forum Mall in Kukatpally, was organised under the aegis of the Telangana Cab Drivers and Owners Association (TCDOA).
Midday meal and ASHA workers held a protest outside Agriculture Minister OP Dhankar’s house in Jhajjar on Saturday over the attitude of the government to their demands.
Midday meal and ASHA workers organised a procession to the office of Dharam Pal Sharma, state BJP vice-president, in Kaithal on Saturday, in support of their demands.

An ex-chairman of Gurugram block committee from Shikohpur village (Congress) and his supporters reportedly thrashed an employee and ransacked the Kherki Daula toll plaza on Delhi-Gurugram Expressway on Saturday.

An angry mob of Bahujan Samaj Party (BSP) supporters pelted stones at Samajwadi Party (SP) legislator Shahid Manzoor on Saturday during polling at the Islamia Madarsa poling booth in Meerut's Kithaur constituency. The police resorted to cane charge to disperse the unruly crowd.
Members of an action council in Kozhikode turned up in large numbers and staged a protest over the murder of Infosys software engineer Rasila in her office in Pune last month.
At least twenty people were injured, three of them critically, when farmers of two neighbouring districts clashed in Chorsundarpur in Nadia district today.
Several incidences of stone pelting and clashes were reported during the first of seven phases of the Assembly Elections in Uttar Pradesh on Saturday.
The students of Lucknow University new campus locked the gates of the faculty of law and staged protest on Saturday while alleging that they were deliberately given poor marks by the examiners.
Supporters of the Samajwadi Party (SP) and Bahujan Samaj Party (BSP) clashed on Saturday in Meerut city of Uttar Pradesh over issues relating to voting.

A poll-related clash between supporters of Bharatiya Janata Party and BSP was reported at DAV Inter College in Kankarkhera area of Meerut on Saturday afternoon. A scuffle led to brick-batting between the two groups.
A poll-related clash between supporters of Bharatiya Janata Party and Rashtriya Lok Dal was reported at booth no. 124 of Naujheel in Mathura district on Saturday afternoon.
Striking cab drivers continued their hunger strike at Jantar Mantar against mobile-based cab aggregators Ola and Uber. The protesters disrupted cab services across New Delhi on Saturday. Day 2
On Saturday, Candidates protested in front of the Bihar Public Service Commission (BPSC) office for not having received their admit cards a day before the preliminary exam on Sunday.
Following the emerging of a video showing a Congress worker from Bhai Rupa village being forced to strip by police men, Congress workers held a protest over the issue at Rampura on Saturday.

Members of the Jamhuri Adhikar Sabha, Punjab, held a protest against the registration of “false cases” against its members in Sangrur on Saturday. They demanded immediate release of the arrested community members and the cancellation of FIRs.

column23: UNI (United News of India), Times of India (Electronic Edition)
column24: Minor poll-related clash between supporters of SP and BJP was reported from Ferozabad during the first of seven phases of the Assembly Elections in Uttar Pradesh on Saturday. One BJP worker was injured in the violence.

Firozabad zila panchayat president from Samajwadi Party Vijay Pratap Yadav along with his supporters allegedly assaulted BJP Braj area president Suman Chaturvedi in front of cops inside a police station in Shikohabad on Saturday.

The District Parents Association held a protest over “arbitrary” fee charges by schools and other institutions at Sriganganagar on Saturday during a visit of Rajasthan Minister for Mining Surinderpal Singh at a model school in the area.

Congress workers in Ujjain burnt an effigy of the BJP state government over the arrest of BJP's youth wing leader for his alleged involvement in an ISI spy ring busted by Anti-Terrorism Squad (ATS) in Bhopal recently.

Four shopkeepers sustained serious injuries youth of the Deha community allegedly attacked them with swords and daggers at the main market of Trivedi Camp Mubarikpur on Saturday. The matter flared up over the issue of a girl, who belonged to the Deha community and alleged that one of the shopkeepers passed lewd remarks against her

A District Reserve Group constable was injured during an encounter with Naxals in the forests near Pentapad village in Chhattisgarh's Sukma district. The gun fight occurred after a patrol group was ambushed.

Congress workers led by GPCC president Bharatsinh Solanki protested and formed a human chain at Income Tax Circle (assumed in Ahmedabad) on Sunday against the Naliya rape scandal. The workers were detained after they tore down a banner of PM Modi's women felicitation event next month.
Residents staged a protest against the Municipal Corporation Bathinda (MCB) over sewage overflow in the Amarpura Basti area in Bathinda city on Sunday.
The residents of the EWS houses in Sector 26, Chandigarh, on Sunday protested against the MC and the UT Administration for not providing basic amenities in the area.
AAP worker protesting against the Naliya rape scandal outside the CM's bungalow in Gandhinagar on Sunday were detained by the police.
A Congress Bhagwanpur to Haridwar roadshow on Sunday allegedly led to clashes between the activists of BJP and Congress in some areas through which the road-show passed.
Protests occurred in Hyderabad in support of Fatima Nafees, the mother of missing Jawaharlal Nehru University student Najeeb Ahmed. They were demanding a thorough investigation into the case.

column9: AIJASS: All India Jat Aarakshan Sangharsh Samiti
column24: Protesters from All India Jat Aarakshan Sangharsh Samiti sat on a dharna at Jassia village on Rohtak Highway, demanding quota for Jats in central government jobs among others. On Sunday, youths brandishing guns and sharp agricultural equipment took out rallies. Day 15

Holding placards and shouting slogans to stop concretisation work on the Poisar river, over 30 members of the River March, a citizens initiative seeking revival of Mumbai's rivers, launched a River Satyagraha from Thakur complex, Kandivali (east).

Led by former MLA and member of the state BJP executive Rakesh Pathania, a large number of farmers from Thapkor, Khanni and Nagabari gram panchayats gheraoed a police check-post at Kandwal under the Nurpur police station jurisdiction for 45 minutes on Sunday evening and raised anti-police slogans to protest against the unabated illegal mining in their area.

Hundreds of students from Lucknow University and the Darul Uloom Nadwatul Ulama participated in a protest march, led by Fatima Nafees, mother of missing Jawaharlal Nehru University student Najeeb Ahmed, in Lucknow on Sunday. Demanding a thorough investigation into the incident, they raised slogans against Prime Minister Narendra Modi, home minister Rajnath Singh, the Bharatiya Janata Party and the Rashtriya Swayamsewak Sangh.

On Sunday, many BPSC candidates at D.B.R.K. Jalan High School, Patna City staged a protest at the examination centre against delay in distribution of question papers. A large number of examinees from across the state had burnt documents and computers in the IT cell of the BSEB office on Sunday.
Fishermen in Vaithikuppam village, Puducherry, put up an hour long road blockade in protest against the "increasing rowdy menace" in their village.

Residents of 26 villages held a meeting at Raipur village on Sunday, to protest their merger into Municipal Corporation of Sonepat. They demanded the merger be cancelled and gram panchayats restored in villages.

Protests occurred in two cities in Kerala in support of Fatima Nafees, the mother of missing Jawaharlal Nehru University student Najeeb Ahmed. They were demanding a thorough investigation into the case.
Son of Fazilka Central Cooperative Bank vice-chairman and BJP leader Dhanpat Siyag of Waryamkhera village in Abohar was burnt alive in his car on Sunday night on the Hanumangarh mega highway.
On Sunday, Maoists shot dead two villagers and injured three others at Ramnitand village under Bhelwaghati police station of Giridih district.
Sardarpura police allegedly tortured a man arrested for car theft on February 12 night. He was admitted to a hospital.

A BJP worker was hacked to death late at night in the Mukkattukara area of Thrissur during celebrations at a temple. The BJP state unit alleged the Communist Party of India (Marxist) was behind the incident and called for a strike in the district the following day.

A Naxal was killed during an encounter between Maoists and a joint police patrol near the Talperu river in Chhattisgarh's Bijapur district. Two IED's had been triggered by the Maoists, who ambushed the patrol. The latter returned fire.

Over 200 parents of the HBK School, Memnagar locality in Ahmedabad, held a protest on Monday alleging the school failed to get CBSE affiliation despite promising it at the time of admitting their children into the pre-school.
Aizawl City College Students' Union staged a protest rally in Aizawl on Monday in support of their fellow students sent to the alleged fake institution.

Members of various employees association staged a protest outside the Deputy Commissioner’s office in Amritsar on Monday. They demanded that a committee should be constituted to look into problems faced by them during election duty.

A clash between the workers of the Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP) and Congress supporters broke out this evening at Andro Assembly constituency, after Congress supporters stormed the house of a BJP worker and abducted one family member.
In Ara, the students gheraoed the principal of H D Jain college and in Vaishali and they blocked NH-103 and ransacked Samta College. In Motihari, the agitating students blocked NH-28.
In Ara, students gheraoed the principal of H D Jain college and in Vaishali and they blocked NH-103 and ransacked Samta College. In Motihari, the agitating students blocked NH-28.

Members of the Technical and Mechanical Employees Union, under the leadership of Pyare Lal Chughe Kalan, staged a protest in front of the District Administrative Complex over their demands. Their demands are related to completion of service rules, execution of death cases and others.

Members of the non-teaching staff union staged a protest against the management of Punjabi University and the state government over the delay in the release of their last month’s salary on the campus of Punjabi University Regional Centre  in Bathinda on Monday.

Incidents like ballot paper snatching, group clashes, setting fire to the ballot boxes and disruption of election process were reported in some places here and the Commission had sought a detailed report on the incidents from the District Collector.
On Monday, poll violence was reported in different parts of the state. In Brahmagiri, three persons were injured in a case of poll violence, while the husband of a sarpanch candidate was attacked.
Midday meal employees and cooks launched a state-level hunger strike in Chandigarh on Monday to protest non-fulfilment of their demands.
Striking extension lecturers working in government colleges of the state held a demonstration outside the Department of Higher Education in Chandigarh, in support of their demands.
Activists of Jharkhand Mukti Morcha (JMM) on Monday staged a daylong dharna to protestagainst the property tax collection near Randhir Verma Chowk.

The All Adivasi Students' Association of Assam staged a demonstration today at Dispur Last Gate. They were demanding hike in the daily wages of tea workers to Rs 330 and fulfil its demand for ST status to tea garden community in the state.

On Monday, poll violence was reported in different parts of the state. In Kendrapara district, unidentified assailants looted a ballot box from a polling booth of Jagdalpur panchayat and threw it into the river.

Sahibabad residents and members of Hindu Raksha Dal staged a protest and blocked the Delhi-Wazirabad Road in Ghaziabad for nearly half an hour on Monday after they allegedly found remains of a slaughtered cow in Sikandarpur village in Sahibabad. The protesters demanded strict action against the culprits.

Striking cab drivers protesting against mobile-based cab aggregators Ola and Uber resorted to vandalism at a dharna spot near Vaishali, Kaushambi Metro stations in Ghaziabad. The protesters stopped the operating cabs, broke windscreens and punctured car tyres. Day 4

Residents staged a candle march in Ghaziabad on February 13, demanding that the police trace a 12-year-old missing girl immediately and book those responsible. The protest turned violent as two shanties of daily wage workers and domestic helps were burned down by two protesters.

Hundreds of trained home guards from various districts of the state, along with Special Police Officer (SPO) personnel, assembled at Dispur here on Monday morning and started raising slogans against the state government for its constant apathy towards them.
Police arrested the students of the Telangana Left Student Organisations who were protesting the Gurukul Notification issue at the Telangana State Public Service Commission in Hyderabad.

At least four persons were injured as Congress workers, demanding investigation of alleged links of BJP general secretary Kailash Vijayvargiya with Dhruv Saxena (one of the 11 people arrested on the charge of spying for Pakistan) clashed with BJP workers in Indore.
A delegation of villagers from Karora forcible entered the office of the Superintendent of Police (SP) at the mini-secretariat in Kaithal on Monday and allegedly damaged office decorum.
A poll-related clash broke out between the supporters of BJP candidate from Kotdwar Harak Singh Rawat and his opponent Surendra Singh Negi of the Congress late on Monday night.

On Monday, around nine persons were reported injured in poll-related violence in Manipur's Thoubal. The incident took place when police tried to control a confrontation between supporters of BJP and Congress over the holding of an election meeting at Lamdaibung area in between Khangabok and Sangaiyumpham localities.
Sporadic poll related violence have started in the state as state prepares for a two-phase elections on March 4 and 8 next. Some people today allegedly attacked some houses at Imphal West areas.
Protesters set ablaze the office of the sub-divisional officer (civil) at Likabali in Arunachal Pradesh, demanding that Likabali be made the headquarters of Lower Siang district.

A group of BCom students locked the main gate and the administrative office of the Lucknow University on Monday morning, demanding more gap between their examinations. During their three-hour protest, the students raised anti-university slogans and did not allow the university officials, students and faculty to enter the campus from the main gate.
In Ara, the students gheraoed the principal of H D Jain college and in Vaishali and they blocked NH-103 and ransacked Samta College. In Motihari, the agitating students blocked NH-28.

On Monday, poll violence was reported in different parts of the state. In Reng village under Bureshwar panchayat of Nuapada district, tension erupted after some unidentified assailants barged into booth no. 12, poured petrol onto the ballot box and torched it.

As part of the Udupi district bandh called to protest a collection toll on the national highway, a large number of protesters who had gathered at Padubidri started to march towards Hejamady, but were persuaded to stop by local administration.

Teaching and non-teaching employees of Punjabi University held a protest outside the Vice-Chancellor's office in Patiala on Monday, against the re-employment of teachers. They marched towards the Patiala-Rajpura highway, where they burnt the V-C’s effigy after blocking traffic for a few minutes.

Students held protests on Monday and blocked Frazer road in Patna. A section of Intermediate examinees created a ruckus at B D College here on Monday to protest non-issuance of admit cards by Bihar School Examination Board (BSEB). The agitating students ransacked the college furniture and broke the glass panes of the conference hall.

25 BJP party volunteers were arrested after the local unit organised several demonstrations in Puducherry to condemn the Congress Vice-president Rahul Gandhi for his remarks against Prime Minister Narendra Modi. eld a demonstration at the Kamaraj Statue Junction. The protests were held simultaneously at the Indira Gandhi square, Kamaraj Statue Junction, Rajiv Gandhi Square, and Employment Exchange among other places. The arrests were made after they attempted to burn the photographs of Rahul Gandhi.
The effigy of deputy CM was burnt at Tamenglong Bazar as a protest for his 'anti-Naga' utterances.

Around 100 women from Kalwa and Vitawa blocked the train tracks in Thane for 15 minutes to protest the sealing of 99 illegal building on the MIDC land at Digha, which falls under the jurisdiction of Navi Mumbai Municipal Corporation (NMMC). Police arrived to stop the protest, but no arrests were made.
Local BJP leaders led demonstrations in Villianur, Puducherry, to condemn the Congress Vice-president Rahul Gandhi for his remarks against Prime Minister Narendra Modi.
BJP candidate Mahendra Bhatt was rushed to the hospital after being attacked by unknown persons in the early hours on Monday.
Hindu Jagran Manch staged a protest against Valentine's Day in Agra on Tuesday.

Vadaj police on Tuesday detained 29 members of Bajrang Dal who protested against Valentine Day celebrations at a garden at Usmanpura locality of Ahmedabad city and some college campuses on Ashram Road.
Locals of Aimol Ngairong village under Tengnoupal district protested against the proposed transfer of 3rd IRB post from their area today.

Residents of nearby villages held a dharna at the bus stand of Bhalian village near Rupnagar on Tuesday, demanding a ban on the plying of heavy vehicles (including tippers carrying sand and gravel) on the Ropar-Bela road.
The Odisha Medical Employees' Association staged a dharna in front of the MKCG Medical College Hospital Superintendent's office on Tuesday.

Women teachers of the Government Adarsh Senior Secondary School, Pacca village in Faridkot, staged an indefinite protest outside Faridkot SSP's office on Tuesday over the chairman of the school allegedly misbehaving with them and using lewd language.

Students of the MR Government College, affiliated to Panjab University, staged a dharna outside the office of Deputy Commissioner in Fazilka, against the recent examination fee hike by the Panjab University.
The strike by drivers of app-based cab aggregators turned violent late on Tuesday night as some unidentified protesters set a cab afire near Green Valley in Indirapuram, Ghaziabad. Day 5

A group took out a march at Kaduthuruthi in Kottayam district, demanding that their favorite liquor outlet be retained. Bevco outlets had been relocated as per an order to remove them from the side of highways.

Locals held a day-long protest against a meat cold storage unit in northwest Delhi's Keshav Puram on Tuesday, alleging that the storage owners were storing cow meat inside. The protesters stopped a truck bringing meat into the storage and detained the driver.
A clash broke out today when the supporters of BJP of Khangabok prevented a camera meeting of INC from taking place at Charapur public ground of Khangabok Part 3 under Khangbok constituency.

The district unit of the Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) protested the Haryana government’s decision to include a ‘caste’ column in public recruitment forms in Kurukshetra on Tuesday. AAP activists handed over a memorandum to the district administration in this regard.

Five persons were injured following a clash between people of Mokhana village of Bhuj in Kutch and PGVCL officials on Tuesday morning. The PGVCL officials along with a police team had gone to check power thefts at the village. As tension built up, over 100 villagers gathered at the spot and a police sub-inspector opened fire to disburse the crowd. This enraged the villagers who started pelting stones on police vehicles.
The Bajrangi Dal activists on Tuesday thrashed couples in Bihar's Muzaffarpur in a protest against Valentine's Day.

Hundreds of farmers, under the banner of Karnataka Sugarcane Growers Association, staged a demonstration in front of the DC's Office in Mysore, seeking fulfilment of their demands. Earlier, traffic on Sayyaji Rao Road was disrupted for over 30 minutes, as farmers squatted in front of MCC Office while persuading police to let them continue to the DC's office.

Thousands of All Assam Students' Union AASU activists of Ghograpar Anchalik Students' Union today blocked the NH 31 at Ghograpar in protest against the government's failure to supply textbooks to students till date.

Members of the Jawaharlal Nehru University Students Union (JNUSU) along with teachers, took out a protest march to the Parliament on Tuesday, demanding revocation of the May 5 2016 regulations on the new admission process. Protesting students have also been sitting on a hunger strike and a dharna at the administrative building on campus. Day 6
Five teachers of the school at Pakka staged a protest outside the SSP's office on Tuesday, demanding action against the chairman Sukhsagar Avenue Welfare Association for sexual harassment.

Members of the Safai Mazdoor Union staged a protest and burnt an effigy of the district administration in Rampura Phul on Tuesday, demanding the arrest of those accused of killing the 58-year-old safai sewak.

At least seven policemen, including district superintendent of police RV Asari, were on Tuesday injured in stone pelting, when cops tried to stop a farmers' rally near Sanand town in Gujarat. Police resorted to lathicharge and lobbed tear gas shells when protesters turned against them. Some 3,000 farmers from 35 villages near Nal Sarovar had participated in the rally to raise the issue of water supply.

Six to seven unidentified men attacked local Congress leader Manoj Mhatre with swords before shooting him to death outside his Bhiwandi residence. Police later arrested several men, among them the cousin of the deceased. It is assumed that the killing was part of a political rivalry.

Two Special Task Force (STF) personnel were killed in a fire exchange with naxalites in Chhattisgarh's Kondagaon district. The fire fight took place in the Tumdiwal forest area, and it is believed that several Maoists were killed as well, although those deaths were not confirmed.

Bank Mitras (Business Correspondents) engaged by a government sector bank staged a protest against Punjab National Bank outside its circle office in Amritsar on Wednesday, alleging that the bank management was exploiting them.

Police attempted to control a large crowd in Bengaluru which was stoning the cars in AIADMK General Secretary V K Sasikala's convoy, and the cars of her followers. She was travelling from Chennai to surrender herself to authorities.
Over 200 residents of BBMP's Mahadevapura Zone took part in a protest march in the morning between 9 AM to 11 AM morning on Borewell Road in Whitefield, Bengaluru, against a lack of civic amenities.

Over 100 temple priests, and religious figures performed havan and other religious ceremonies at the Kamla Park Road in Bhopal and blocked one side of the road to register their protest. They were demonstrating against the Uttar Pradesh State Government's upcoming ordinance concerning the takover of all temple land in the state.

A minor poll-related clash between SP and BSP workers was reported from Bijnor during the second phases of the Assembly Elections in Uttar Pradesh on Wednesday. Seven people were injured in the incident.
Jharkhand Mukti Morcha party workers burnt the effigy of Das in Bokaro on Wednesday. They also criticised the Global Investor Summit (GIS) beginning from February 16 in Ranchi.
A minor poll-related clash between SP and BJP workers was reported from Badaun during the second phases of the Assembly Elections in Uttar Pradesh on Wednesday.

Residents of Sector 44 gathered at the roundabout of Sectors 43 and 44 in Chandigarh to protest the removal of the rotary. The protestors demanded that the rotary should be constructed again and the traffic lights be made functional at the earliest.
BJP workers staged a protest at Chandni Chowk locality of New Delhi on Wednesday and burnt effigy of the Arvind Kejriwal-led AAP government accusing it of corruption and inefficiency.
Minor incidences of poll-related clashes were reported during the Uttarakhand assembly elections on Wednesday.

Local residents, including students and staff of a private school adjacent to the spot, staged a protest against the move of the Haryana Urban Development Authority (HUDA) to remove 28 green trees on a two-acre plot in Sector 15, Faridabad, on Tuesday.

They were demanding the registration of a case against Kotkapura Akali MLA Mantar Singh Brar and Kotkapura Market Committee chairman Jaspal Singh Maur for harassing the deceased.
In Golaghat, students also burnt the effigy of Mr Patowary. Students and activists staged protests on Wednesday across the state including Jorhat, Golaghat, Sonitpur and Guwahati.

A protest programme was organised today on the bank of the Dighalipukhuri demanding justice for the girl who was allegedly molested in Jorhat recently. Hundreds of people, including students from various educational institutions, took part in the protest programme.
Hundreds of Anganwadi workers today staged a demonstration at the Social Welfare directorate at Uzanbazar here.
The Kamrup (metro) and Darrang district units of Asam Sahitya Sabha today protested against the attack on the Sabha's former general secretary Paramananda Rajbongshi.
The women's wing of Assam Pradesh Congress Committee staged a protest on Wednesday seeking justice for Subh Laxmi and Patowary's resignation.

Media reports about the questioning of a police officer triggered a protest by residents of Khurai. The protesters blocked the Imphal-Ukhrul road on Wednesday and held a demonstration at the gate of local CBI office here yesterday. [Day 1]

Students and activists staged protests on Wednesday across the state including Jorhat, Golaghat, Sonitpur and Guwahati. They questioned the minister whether the sexual harassment was prompted by the victim's leftist ideology.

BJP workers staged a protest at Karol Bagh locality of New Delhi on Wednesday and burnt effigy of the Arvind Kejriwal-led AAP government accusing it of corruption and inefficiency.

The West Bengal College and University Teachers Association held a protest yesterday against Education Bill passed in the state assembly.

They stormed the hospital, beat up a doctor, broke glass windows and damaged several computers and laboratory equipment. Police along with RAF personnel was deployed at the hospital.

Organised by the Shopkeeper's Welfare Association of the Tipu Sultan Mosque.
At Konni in Pathanamthitta, local Congress legislator and bar owner Adoor Prakash led a mass protest against shifting of a Bevco liquor outlet to the area.
BJP workers staged a protest at Laxmi Nagar locality of New Delhi on Wednesday and burnt effigy of the Arvind Kejriwal-led AAP government accusing it of corruption and inefficiency.

Gujjars staged protests at Bansur in Alwar district on Thursday over the Special Backward Classes (SBC) quota issue.

Residents of Guru Gobind Singh Nagar and the adjoining Dhillon Colony protested in Bathinda on Thursday, against trucks illegally parked not only on the main road but also in the by-lanes of the area.

Senior officers of four financial institutions staged a sit-in outside the house of CE Fernandese, chairman of GEI Power Limited, adjacent to Ashima Mall, Hoshangabad Road in Bhopal "to mount social and moral pressure on the businessman to repay loans".

Farmers under the banner of the Haryana Poplar-Safeda Utpadak Sangharsh Samiti staged a protest in Chhachhrauli town of Yamunanagar district on Thursday against the falling rates of poplar wood. Whenbthe farmers tried to burn the wood, the police started arresting them.

column9: IPFT: Indigenous People's Front of Tripura
column24: Yesterday, protestors ransacked the party office of CPI(M) in the area and chased away a few local CPI(M) leaders when they insisted some shopkeepers to open their business opposing the strike. At least seven TSR jawans were injured when IPFT called for a strike.

Media reports about the questioning of a police officer triggered a protest by residents of Khurai. The protesters blocked the Imphal-Ukhrul road on Wednesday and held a demonstration at the gate of local CBI office here yesterday. [Day 2]

Hundreds of teaching aspirants burnt their State Eligibility Test (SET)-2017 admit cards in front of Madhya Pradesh Public Service Commission's office in Indore. They demanded the dates of the test to be changed as it is based on the National Eligibility Test (NET) pattern during which a period of six months is given to the candidates after they apply for the examination.
Mid-day meal workers protested outside the DC office in Jalandhar on Thursday, against the non-allocation of any allowance to the polling staff in exchange for the food cooked by them

A large number of residents of Karora, Kukar Kanda and other villages staged a protest at the Mini-Secretariat in Kaithal on Thursday, demanding the arrest of the accused in the murder case of Vikas, a resident of Karora village.

Delhi BJP Mahila Morcha workers held a massive demonstration at the residence of Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal to protest against the government's ''non-performance'' on the issues like women safety and creation of jobs for women, in Delhi on Thursday. Delhi Police resorted to water cannons as hundreds of women demonstrators broke double police barricade around the Chief Minister's residence and ran towards it.

Two leaders of the striking cap drivers who are sitting on a hunger strike at Jantar Mantarvin New Delhi since a week, were admitted to RML Hospital in view of their deteriorating condition on Thursday. The protesters demands include non-lowering of rates, life insurance for drivers and non-preference for taxis owned by the firms. Day 7

Ajay Maken, Delhi Congress president, and all the sitting Congress councillors of the civic bodies staged a protest at SP Mukherjee Civic Centre on Thursday afternoon over 'non-payment of arrears to sanitation workers and pensions to the widows, handicapped and senior citizens.

Bus drivers of the Maharashtra State Road Transport Corporation (MSRTC) in Pune held a chakka jam and locked down the Chinchwad depot for four hours after one of their colleagues was allegedly thrashed to death by a driver of a private vehicle.

Striking extension lecturers working in government colleges of the state held a demonstration outside the office of Randhir Singh Kaprivaas, local MLA, in Rewari on Thursday, in support of their demands.

A CRPF personnel was injured in the explosion of a pressure bomb planted by Naxals in Chhattisgarh’s Bijapur district. The incident took place in the Mahadev Ghati area when a team of CRPF’s 229th battalion was on patrolling duty.
Following the gang rape of a 15-year-old Dalit girl, Dalits staged a protest in Abohar.
Congress workers allegedly resorted to vandalism during the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC) special board meeting to clear the budget for 2017/18 on Friday.

Bank staffers led by the The Aurangabad District Bank Employees Association staged an agitation in front of the State Bank of India (SBI) zonal office in Aurangabad against the merger of associated banks with SBI.

The visually impaired students enrolled in various courses of vocational training at National Institute for Empowerment of Persons with Visual Disabilities (NIEPVD) staged a protest march on the NIEPVD campus in Dehradun on Friday, over non payment of pocket money and non receipt of laptops.

The Goalpara unit of the All Assam Students Union (AASU), supported by the AllAssam Rabha Students Union (ARSU), along with local people staged a protest demonstration in front of the Deputy Commissioner's office here today.

Women of Khurai area took out a torch rally today in protest against the failure of the state government to punish the culprits involved in the 'Sanjit fake encounter case' and 'Tulihal drug case'.

Volunteers of the All Manipur Students' Union (AMSU) today stormed the offices of political parties in Imphal including Congress and BJP demanding disclosure of the framework agreement signed between government of India and NSCN(IM).

The death of a school driver deployed for poll duty sparked protest from fellow drivers who took to streets, pelting stones and damaging as many as six buses and vehicles at Kila Crossing near Smriti Upvan in Aashiana locality of Lucknow city on Friday evening. They were demanding compensation. The situation was brought under control after deployment of two companies of the PAC.
