South Delhi BJP MP Ramesh Bidhuri led a demonstration near Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal's residence in New Delhi on Friday to protest poor state of government schools.
Animal lovers continued to protest on Friday after a street dog was beaten to death with a stick, allegedly by a security guard at the Delhi Technological University (DTU) in Rohini on Thursday.

The Fourlane Sangharsh Samiti Mandi-Kullu staged a protest against the state government and the National Highways Authority of India (NHAI) at Pandoh in Mandi on Friday. They were demanding compensation against land according to the Land Acquisition Act, 2013.
One faction of the employees of Punjabi University blocked the Patiala-Rajpura national highway for five hours in Patiala on Friday, seeking relieving of the re-employed teachers of the university

Similarly, Dangari, Saikhowa, Kakopothar and Phillobari units of AASU under Doomdooma circle also staged the protest at their respective places. Moreover, Sadiya sub-division unit of the students' body also organised the programme at Chapakhowa.

After the posters were torn, the organisers gathered in huge numbers at the Valpoi police station at midnight, and started demonstrating and shouting slogans. Police tried to stop the organisers and participants from taking out a rally through the city, ensuing in high drama. The situation remained tense as around 200 policemen were deployed and the police has urged the citizens to maintain law and order.

A 58-year-old employee of ministry of defence was seriously injured after being shot at in Crossings Republik area on Saturday afternoon over a property dispute. The victim sustained two bullet injuries and is in a critical condition.

1 Maoist was killed and two weapons were recovered after an exchange of fire took place between an STF and DRG patrol and Maoists in the Dabbamarka and Pottakpalli area of Sukma district, Chhattisgarh.
Naxals triggered a landmine in the Kaligonda forest area of Chinturu, East Godavari district, near a passing patrol of 40 police personnel. However none of them were injured.

At least 40 BJP workers were detained by police at Limbayat and Parvat Patia areas of Surat city for protesting against Gujarat Pradesh Congress Committee president Bharatsinh Solanki, who was in the city on Sunday to participate in a rally organized by BJP councillor Ranvindra Patil to celebrate the birth anniversary of Chhatrapati Shivaji.

The Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) held demonstration at Raman Mandi in Talwandi Sabo on Sunday, against Prime Minister Narendra Modi government’s decision of demonetisation on the 100th day after its launch in the country.

column9: AIJASS: All India Jat Aarakshan Sangharsh Samiti
column24: All India Jat Aarakshan Sangharsh Samiti intensified its agitation for Jat quotas on February 19 and observed 'Balidan Diwas' at Umrakheri village near the Panipat-Shamli in remembrance of the protesters who died on the same day last year. Day 22

Incidents of violence were reported from several places across the state after the fourth phase polling and counting of votes yesterday. A defeated ward member candidate, Kameswar Palakka, was murdered in Maoist-dominated Bandhugaon area of Koraput district. Incidents of violence were also reported in Bhadrak, Jajpur, Kendrapara, Nayagarh and Khurda districts.
A Congress member died in an accident, allegedly staged by BJD activists.
Members of the Attari Truck Union launched an indefinite dharna near the Integrated Check Post (ICP) in Amritsar on Monday.
Residents of Guru Gobind Singh Nagar and Ballaram Nagar protested outside the Triveni Company’s office in Bathinda on Monday, over not getting water for third consecutive day.
Non-teaching staff members of Punjabi University’s regional centre staged a protest on the premises of the centre in Bathinda on Monday, against the re-employment of teachers mid-session.

Students of Kaji Shah Madrasa at Beldanga in Murshidabad district of West Bengal today staged a demonstration at the educational institute and blocked a nearby road for hours. When police tried to lift the road blockade, students clashed with the cops and ransacked a police vehicle.
Family members of a retired Bokaro Steel employee staged a protest before the corporate hospital on Monday, alleging it had given the septuagenarian expired cardiac medicines.

Protesters took out a rally in Chamarajanagar, demanding that the authorities arrest arsonists responsible for damaging a temple chariot, and take necessary measures to repair it before Ashadha month when rathothsava is celebrated.

column9: NSUI: National Students' Union of India
column24: Activists of the National Students’ Union of India held a demonstration in Dehradun on Monday and demanded extension in dates for submitting examination forms.

The Gujarat Congress ended its three-day "Beti Bachao Yatra" (protest rally) over the Naliya rape scandal from Naliya in Kutch to Gandhinagar on February 20. They demanded an independent probe into the case by a High Court judge. Over 200 Congress members were detained after they took out a rally in Gandhinagar. Day 3
Aam Aadmi Party workers held protests over the Naliya rape scandal at various places in Gujarat state on Monday. Some 400 AAP workers were detained across the state.

A section of striking drivers employed by app-based aggregators stopped cabs near Shankar Chowk in Gurgaon and also partially blocked vehicles on Monday to protest against the app-based aggregators Ola and Uber. Police officers arrived at the spot and brought situation under control.
Hundreds of parents whose children attend the Salwan Public School protested against a mid-year fee hike at the district education office in Gurgaon on Monday morning.
Shopkeepers at Badshahpur market in Gurgaon staged a protest on Monday against the poor law and order situation in the area. shopkeepers blocked the Sohna Road.

Hundreds of mining labourers rendered jobless after a ban on mining in the Aravali ranges in Bhiwani district staged a protest and locked Bhiwani Mahendergarh MP Dharambir Singh’s house in Hisar on Monday.
Residents of Daulowal village staged a protest at the site of the Century Plywood factory on Monday night, demanding that night-time construction work be stopped.

A group of Jat Jagriti Sena (JJS) activists, who have been observing an indefinite hunger strike in Rohtak, staged an agitation and submit a memorandum to ADC Narhari Bangar in Jhajjar on Monday, demanding withdrawal of cases registered against Jats last year.

12 BJP cadres were injured after BJP leaders and hundreds of party supporters began agitating outside Mahaveer Nagar police station, and clashed with police. The police had to resort to lathicharge to disperse them. Additional force was called at the spot to control the agitation with the police blocking all the ways leading to the police station. At some places, the workers burnt tyres and damage the vehicles parked in the area. The agitation began after the husband of BJP MLA Chandra Kanta Meghwal slapped a police officer and a scuffle ensued.

Akhil Bharatiya Khet Mazdoor Union, MGNREGA Kamgar Union and other organisations held a 'Akrosh’ rally and took out a protest march to the DC camp office in Karnal on Monday, demanding the implementation of the MGNREGA provisions, including minimum hundred days work and compensation for delayed payment.

People staged a protest at a foreign education consultant company office at Kartarpur town in Jalandhar on Monday, alleging that an agent of the office stole lakhs of rupees that the protesters had given for their migration to Canada.

Workers of the Communist Party of India-Marxist (CPM) staged a protest at Kasumpati on Monday against the state Congress government and the NDA government at the Centre for not providing relief to poor and needy persons who continued to face hardships due to demonetisation.

Hundreds of BJP party workers staged a protest at a police station in Kota on Monday, over a vehicle challan issued to a worker. The protest took an ugly turn when protesters started pelting cops with stones and they resorted to lathicharge to disperse the mob. Around 10 persons, including cops, received minor injuries.

Following a clash between BJP workers and the police in Kota, BJP leaders along with others staged a protest at Mahaveer Nagar police station on Monday until the early hours on Tuesday, demanding action against police officers.
Angry passengers protested against late arrival of trains at Charbagh railway station in Lucknow city, as several trains were 3-9 hours behind schedule.

Supporters of noted gangster Lovely Lamba resorted to protest and vandalism across Ludhiana city, expressing their resentment over his arrest. Over 100 supporters created a ruckus on the streets, blocking, traffic, closing down shops and destroying public property. The protest took a violent turn as protestors took to open firing in the area. The police resorted to lathi charge to disperse the crowd.

A team of Punjab State Power Corporation Limited (PSPCL) was allegedly attacked by villagers when it had gone to check power theft and illegal connections in Mahiana Wala village of Ferozepur district on Monday.

A group of retired paramilitary forces officials held a protest at Jantar Mantar on Monday and took out a march towards Parliament, demanding grant of special pay, OROP and restoration of old pension scheme for lakhs of personnel.
Residents of Shivpuri Mohalla in Phagwara along with a dowry victim, Gurdeep Kaur, and her father Tersem Lal, staged a dharna before the SP Office on Monday, demanding to book in-laws of the victim.

Workers of the Communist Party of India-Marxist (CPM) staged a protest in Shimla on Monday against the state Congress government and the NDA government at the Centre for not providing relief to poor and needy persons who continued to face hardships due to demonetisation.

Workers of the Communist Party of India-Marxist (CPM) staged a protests at district headquarters of Himachal Pradesh on Monday against the state Congress government and the NDA government at the Centre for not providing relief to poor and needy persons who continued to face hardships due to demonetisation.
Around 100 Aam Aadmi Party workers were detained in Surat on Monday as they staged protests over the Naliya rape scandal.
The Haroli unit of the BJP today staged a protest in front of the office of the Deputy Director of Higher Education (assumed in Una) on Monday, to oppose annual functions during exams.
Seven naxals were killed in an encounter with police forces in the forests Pushpal village, Narayanpur district, Chhattisgarh. A large stash of weapons and ammunition was also discovered.
On Tuesday, a police personnel was injured when unidentified militants attacked the security team of Manipur's Deputy Chief Minister Gaikhangam in Khoupum area under Noney district.

A self-styled sub-zonal commander of CPI (Maoist) was killed in an encounter with security forces in Left wing extremist (LWE)-affected Banka district of Bihar, 254km from state capital Patna, on Tuesday.
A Central Reserve Police Force (CRPF) trooper was injured after he stepped on a Maoist-laid pressure bomb in the forest of Dharampeta, Sukma district.

Teachers under the SSA/RMSA Office Employees Union held a protest and burnt an effigy of the government at the Court Chowk in Amritsar on Tuesday, to highlight the state government’s failure to regularise them.
A BJP leader alleged that two of his workers namely of Andro Leitan Pekfam were severely beaten up by some workers of the rival Congress candidate.
Triveni Company workers staged a protest against the company outside its office in Bathinda on Tuesday, for not providing them equipment for work.

Hundreds of people from the Dalit and tribal community took over 10 major spots in Bhopal to protest against the alleged loose and lenient implementation of child protection acts in the state capital. They formed a human chain and demanded reconsideration child rights laws in Bhopal.
Farmers, under the banner of Bharatiya Kisan Union (BKU), held a protest outside the SDM office in Bijnor on Tuesday to highlight their “hardships”.
Two rival groups entered into a pitched battle at the Baliyatra grounds yesterday, after the unofficial panchayat election results of neighbouring Banki block came in.

The visually impaired students enrolled in various courses of vocational training at National Institute for Empowerment of Persons with Visual Disabilities (NIEPVD) started an indefinite fast in Dehradun on Tuesday, over non payment of pocket money and non receipt of laptops.

The Punjab State Power Corporation Limited (PSPCL) Employees Joint Forum staged a dharna (assumed in Ferozepur) on Tuesday, condemning an assault on their staff in Mahiana Wala village of Ferozepur district on Monday and demanding strict action against the villagers.
Student bodies today staged strong protests against the SEBA's goof-up in distribution of question papers of the HSLC Examination yesterday.

A group of activists held a candlelight vigil in Hauz Khas Village on Tuesday evening to protest the sexual assault of a 26-year-old woman at Deer Park. The protest was organised by Manipur Women Gun Survivors Network (MWGS)

The fathers of students, studying in Shiv Jyoti School in Jalandhar, held a protest on Tuesday morning, against the school administration for allegedly hiking the fee and restricting those students from appearing in the examinations who have failed to deposit the annual charges.

Members of the Rail Coach Factory Employees Union held a demonstration at the Rail Coach Factory in Kapurthala on Tuesday, against the alleged move of the government to outsource and privatise the furnishing shop on the campus.
FCI workers, under the banner of the FCI Workers Union, held a protest on Tuesday in Kartarpur, against the decision to outsource their jobs to a private contractor.
Villagers protested against a sacrilege incident in Khalra village, 45 km from Tarn Taran, on Tuesday.

Following a deadly accident killing a 18-year-old student, fellow students started rioting in Lucknow. They vandalised a tea-stall, damaged an auto and blocked the traffic for hours. The police resorted to mild force to disburse agitating students which left six students with minor injuries.

Members of two communities (Muslims and Valmikis) clashed in the Giaspura locality of Ludhiana city on Tuesday morning. They pelted one another with stones during which several persons suffered injuries. The police had to use mild force to disperse the crowds.

During the polling process in Mumbai, protests took a violent turn in Ward No. 135, Mankhurd area. The police had to resort to lathi-charge to drive away demonstrators protesting against the voters' list.
The relatives of a 28-year-old man, who was found dead, held a protest at Kotkapura Chowk in Muktsar city on Tuesday by placing his body on the road, demanding action against his in-laws.
Scattered clashes occurred between two groups in the Nagpada area of Mumbai during the polling process.
All India Mahila Congress activists staged a protest against Naliya sex scandal outside BJP Head Quarters in New Delhi on Tuesday.

The Akhil Bharatiya Vidyarthi Parishad on Tuesday locked down the Delhi University college’s seminar room and pelted stones in protest against the invitation to the JNU students Umar Khalid and Shehla Rashid, calling them “anti-nationals”.
Striking drivers of app-based cab aggregators took out a protest march from Majnu Ka Tila in North Delhi on Tuesday.

column9: INPT: Indigenous Nationalist Party of Tripura
column24: More than 200 activists of INPT had participated in an 8 -hour sit-in strike in front of Jantar Mantar in Delhi on Tuesday, to press for their demands  including empowerment of ADC by ensuring direct funding.

Over 70 members of 14 dalit families, who are facing social and economic boycott by upper caste members of Par village in Santalpur taluka of Patan, sat on a dharna before the district collector's office in Palanpur on Tuesday demanding relocation to other village.
Two private cars were damaged as the workers of the NCP and Shiv Sena clashed in Baner area of Pune during the polling process.

A clash occurred after police refused to let NCP activists into a polling station in Bopodi, Pune, to cast their votes after 5.30 pm, the closing time. The state reserve police force used lathi-charge to disperse the mob, who were attempting to break into the polling station, and who were attacking the police.

Members of the Balmiki community resorted to a traffic blockade in Rajound town of Kaithal district on Tuesday, to protest the death of a youth in a road accident last night and the alleged delay in police action .
A day after two girls were sexually assaulted by two juveniles in Rohini while defecating in the open, locals staged a protest, demanding better sanitation facilities in the area.
The Bhartiya Kisan Union (Ugrahan) on Tuesday held a protest in Kohriyan (assumed in Sangrur), demanding the arrest of the accused of murdering Gurdev Kaur.

Former minister Narender Bragta with BJP supporters protested outside the Directorate of Horticulture in Shimla on Tuesday, against the state government for allegedly supplying virus-infected imported apple plants and betraying the trust of the people by not implementing the election manifesto.

Large groups of students of Thoubal district today formed a human chain demanding a white paper on the points incorporated in the accord signed between the government of India and the NSCN (IM) on or before February 25. The protest was organised by the All Manipur Students Association (AMSU), Thoubal district.

A day after a 6 year-old boy was allegedly stabbed to death and the body was cut into pieces by a drug addict in Amaria tehsil of Pilibhit district, nearly a thousand local residents came out to the street on Wednesday to protest against the murder and demanded capital punishment for the killer.

The Joint Front of the Central Public Works Department employees staged a protest outside the office of the Executive Engineer, CPWD, on Ram Tirath Road in Amritsar on Wednesday. The employees alleged that some secretaries of the department are forcing corporatisation of the department, which is against the interests of the employees.

Villagers of Kankwal, Malkana, Phulokhari, etc. in Talwandi Sabo constituency of Bathinda sat on a dharna outside the office of the canal department (assumed in Bathinda) on Wednesday over water scarcity.

Residents of nearby villages blocked traffic near Bhalian village in Rupnagar on Wednesday, demanding a ban on the plying of heavy vehicles (including tippers carrying sand and gravel) on the Ropar-Bela road.
More than 1,000 four-wheelers entered Bhopal to participate in a protest led by Congress, causing serious traffic congestion for 8 hours.

CPDW employees comprising engineers, architects and office staff, under the banner of the Joint Front of the CPWD Service Associations, held a mass rally at Kendriya Sadan in Sector 9, Chandgrah, on Wednesday, to protest against the recommendations made by Rajiv Gauba, Secretary, UD to the Prime Minister.
Members of the United Forum of Bank Unions staged a protest against the anti-labour policies of the Union government in Dehradun on Wednesday.

The teaching and non-teaching women staff of Government Adarsh School staged a protest in front of the SSP office in Faridkot, demanding the arrest of the school manager for allegedly harassing woman teachers and forcing students to do labour work.

Teachers, under the banner of All Haryana Extension Lecturers' Association, staged a protest outside Government Women's College in Sector 14, Gurgaon, on Wednesday against the state education minister, demanding an end to the pay-per-lecture practice.

Police arrested scores of students and their leaders after clashes erupted at several rallies led by unemployed students in Hyderabad. Students pelted stones at police, who responded with lathi charges. The protesters were condemning the arrest of Telangana Joint Action Committee (TJAC) convenor M. Kodandaram and other leaders and activists across Telangana.

Students of All Manipur Student Union (AMSU), members of United Committee Manipur (UCM) and Committee of Civil Societies Kangleipak (CCSK) stormed the gate of Imphal Raj Bhawan at Nityaipat Chuthek today All Manipur Students' Union. They were demanding details of the framework agreement signed between the Centre and NSCN (IM).

Hundreds of Congressmen led by former legislator and Congress Jaipur city president Pratap Singh Khachariyawas staged a protest at Vidhyut Bhawan in Jaipur on February 22  to demand roll back of tariff for domestic power.

The Jalandhar unit of Joint Front, a forum of CPWD service associations, held a mass protest rally in Jalandhar on Wednesday, against the Union Government’s proposal to turn the Central Public Works Department into a corporation.
The All Manipur Students Union (AMSU), district committee Jiribam held a rally today against the non-disclosure of framework agreement.
Jodhpur residents staged a protest against the civic body at the ward office on Wednesday, over insufficient water supply.

Over 1,000 people working for commercial organisations located at Panampilly Nagar, Kochi, joined hands for a candlelight march to protest against the possible closure of trade establishments following a high court order.
BJP organised a protest rally in Kullu on Wednesday under the “Mafia Raj Hatao Pradesh Bachao” campaign against the state government and the poor law and order situation in the state.

Archaeologists trying to survey a recently discovered Buddhist site in Ghosikund village of Chanan area in Lakhisarai, ran into a wall of protesters who took to violence to block the site. The protesters want an engineering college to come up instead.
Trauma centre contractual staff staged a protest and locked the gated of the King George's Medical University in Lucknow after one of them was beaten up by attendants of a patient who died.
Following a deadly accident, a number of residents of Panj Graian village near Machhiwara staged a protest on Wednesday, seeking registration of a case against the driver.

Violent clashes broke out between Left-affiliated AISA and RSS-backed ABVP at Delhi University’s Ramjas College on Wednesday over a seminar invite to JNU students Umar Khalid and Shehla Rashid, which left many students, teachers and policemen injured.
Members of Brahmin organisations protested against singer Pradeep Boora at Skylark resort in Panipat on Wednesday, for allegedly using derogatory words against women in his song.

As part of an agitation to condemn the attack on DMK working president MK Stalin in the Tamil Nadu Legislative Assembly, DMK (North) volunteers in Puducherry observed a fast in front of the head post office, while the DMK (South) volunteers observed the fast near the Swadeshi cotton mills.
Khadki Pune, police arrested 40 NCP activists for rioting at a polling booth and attacking police in Bopodi the previous day.

A group of college students demonstrated at the Mini-Secretariat in Rohtak against the removal of the “Jat Shaheed Chowk” boards installed by the JJS at Rajiv Chowk on the Delhi bypass. They also submitted a memorandum to the City Magistrate, demanding the reinstallation of the boards.

Protesting Jat Jagriti Sena (JJS) activists, who have been observing an indefinite hunger strike in Rohtak, tried to oppose the police from moving two elderly protesters whose health has been deteriorating from the dharna site on Wednesday evening. Day 27

The contract/outsourced employees’ joint action committee on Wednesday took out a protest march and burnt the effigy of the state government in Sangrur. They were protesting the delay in the regularisation of their services.

Police arrested scores of students and their leaders at several rallies led by unemployed students in Secunderabad. They were condemning the arrest of Telangana Joint Action Committee (TJAC) convenor M. Kodandaram and other leaders and activists across Telangana.

column9: CITU: Centre of Indian Trade Unions
column24: The police arrested 27 protesting CITU leaders from the gate of the HP Power Corporation (HPPCL) headquarters in Shimla on Wednesday night.
A large number of anganwadi and Asha workers staged a protest at Limbayat MLA Sangita Patil's office in Surat city on Wednesday, over their wage hike.

A demolition drive by the Surat Municipal Corporation (SMC) turned violent in Limbayat area of Surat city on Wednesday with an angry mob pelting stones at SMC vehicles and allegedly manhandling personnel.
Farmers of three villages sat on indefinite dharna in front of the Haryana State Industrial Development Corporation office in Yamunanagar on Wednesday, demanding higher land compensation.

In poll-related violence, the sons and supporters of the rival BSP and SP candidates clashed in Mahoba on Thursday morning during the fourth phase of polling in Uttar Pradesh state, allegedly over distributing cash to voters. Five sustained serious injures.

column8: NSCN-IM: National Socialist Council of Nagaland-Isak-Muivah
column24: Shootouts occurred involving the NSCN-IM, Zeliangrong United Front (ZUF) and security forces today at Khoupum valley, Noney district. The first incident took place between a team of 2/5 GR and NSCN-IM in general area of Chingthak Khoupum. A civilian woman and a cadre of NSCN-IM were reportedly killed and two including one civilian and one cadre of the outfit sustained injuries.

column8: NSCN-IM: National Socialist Council of Nagaland-Isak-Muivah
column24: A second shoot out reportedly took place at Goibijang village in Noney district wherein the NSCN-IM cadres were ambushed by the ZUF. In the attack, two cadres of the NSCN-IM were reportedly injured

On Thursday, TMC workers took part in a civil disobedience movement to press for their demands. Hundreds were arrested from near the Raj Bhavan here and received injuries when police prevented them after breaking second barricade.

Haryana's opposition party INLD organised a massive protest march over the over the issue of defunct Sutlej Yamuna Link (SYL) canal from Amabala towards Kapuri in Patiala on Thursday to dig the SYL canal. Scores of INLD leaders and supporters were detained by the Punjab Police at the inter-state Shambhu barrier, few kilometres from Ambala in Haryana.

Farmers, under the leadership of BKU Sidhupur, staged a protest in front of the office of the senior engineer of the PSPCL in Bathinda on Thursday over their demand for 10-hour regular power supply during the day.

Parents staged a dharna outside the office of the Additional Deputy Commissioner (ADC) at the District Administrative Complex in Bathinda on Thursday, over the dispute pertaining to alleged flouting of the guidelines laid under the Right to Education Act 2009 by schools.

Drivers and conductors of mini-buses being run by the Municipal Corporation Bathinda (MCB) and the PRTC blocked roads outside the bus stand and railway station in Bathinda city on Thursday. They alleged that their business was being affected as auto-rickshaw drivers, in connivance with a few policemen, were picking passengers from main areas in the city. They also protested against the alleged misbehaviour against one of their drivers by the police and auto-rickshaw drivers.

The RSS students' wing ABVP, BJP ally Ajsu and others protested in Daltonganj when CM today laid the foundation stones of three medical colleges in Daltonganj, Dumka and Hazaribagh. The protesters clashed with the police. The protests spilled to Ranchi.

Students of local MR Government College under the banner of the Punjab Students Union (PSU) staged a protest at the college stadium in Fazilka on Thursday, against the hike in examination fee by Panjab University (PU).

Four legislators, including a woman BJP minister, were injured when a clash broke out over farmers suicide in the state inside the Gujarat Assembly between opposition Congress and the ruling party members during the budget session proceedings on Thursday.

Police in Deonar, Mumbai, arrested 1500 people for pelting stones and injuring three policemen at a protest outside the M-East BMC ward office in Govandi. The agitated mob protested and demanded a re-election, since their names did not figure on the voters' list.
A poll-related clash between Congress and Bahujan Samaj Party supporters was reported from Harchandpur constituency on Thursday during the fourth phase of polling in Uttar Pradesh state.
Bengal BJP held a demonstration in front of the state administrative headquarters at Nabanna on Thursday.

Today volunteers of AMSU and KSA agitated at three different places, at Khurai Lamlong, Pureiriomba Khongnangkhong, Palace Compound at Keishampat Takhel Leikai. They were protesting against fake encounters.

Nearly 50 members of the Contract Employees Action Committee, Punjab, held a demonstration at the District Administration Complex in Jalandhar on Thursday, demanding regularisation of their jobs. Protesting employees submitted a memorandum of demands to SDM Rajiv Verma.

Maharashtra Navnirman Sena leader Sanjay Turde was standing outside his office in Kalina, Mumbai, when he and his party members were attacked by more than 50 BJP workers. They were taken to hospital, and the BJP members involved were arrested.

Family members and relatives of Jagdish Paswan, who retired from the Food Corporation of India and died yesterday of illness, staged a dharna and placed the deceased's body outside the FCI office in Kanral on Thursday. They alleged that due to non-payment of Central Provident Fund (CPF) Jagdish could not afford medical treatment.

Family members and relatives of woman and a baby that died during delivery, staged a protest at the hospital in Khanna on Thursday, claiming negligence of the doctors and demanding action against them.

Following a clash between BJP workers and the police in Kota, ex-police personnel led by former ASP Yogendra Joshi participated in a silent protest against the misbehaviour with police by the BJP workers at the SP office (assumed in Kota).
Following a clash between BJP workers and the police in Kota, Congress workers staged a protest against  the BJP workers' misbehaviour with police outside the district collectorate in Kota.
Minor incidences of poll-related clashes and stone pelting were reported during the fourth phase of the Assembly Elections in Uttar Pradesh on Thursday.

Members of the All-India Sikh Students Federation held a protest march on the Sutlej Yamuna Link (SYL) canal issue towards Kapoori village in Patiala on Thursday. Around 80 members were detained near Masingan village, near Devigarh.
A poll-related clash between people and the police was reported from Meja Assembly seat in Allahabad district on Thursday during the fourth phase of polling in Uttar Pradesh state.

All India Students Association (AISA) students staged a dharna against the Delhi Police and the ABVP at the Delhi Police Headquarters at ITO in New Delhi on Thursday, against police “high-handedness” during the violent clashes at Ramjas College on Wednesday.

column9: NSUI: National Students' Union of India
column24: National Students Union of India (NSUI) took out a peace march to Maurice Nagar police station, near the North Campus in New Delhi on Thursday, to protest the violent clash at Ramjas College on Wednesday.
National Students Union of India (NSUI) staged a protest in in New Delhi on Thursday, against the repeat of JNU-like events at Delhi University.
Sanitation workers staged a protest and started stripping in front of the Delhi Secretariat on Thursday, demanding funds for the cash deficient Municipal Corporation of the city.

Cab drivers called off their protest against mobile-based cab aggregators Ola and Uber at Jantar Mantar in New Delhi on Thursday, after the Delhi government and the two companies assured them of fulfilling most of their demands. Day 14

The Bains brothers of the Lok Insaf Party (LIP) along with over 400 supporters held a protest march on the Sutlej Yamuna Link (SYL) canal issue towards Kapoori village in Patiala on Thursday, but were stopped by the Patiala police near the new grain market in Patiala.
After ABVP protested in Daltonganj, the protests spilled to Ranchi.

OBC leader Alpesh Thakor and his supporters staged a protest rally on Thursday, demanding jobs for local youths in industries in the state. A bit to lock down Tata Nano plant in Sanand was foiled by the police and Thakor and about 700 supporters were detained in the area around Sanand town.

Following a protest by OBC leader Alpesh Thakor and his supporters in Sanand region on Thursday, sarpanchs of a few villages held a counter-protest against the agitators claiming that the industrial projects had actually increased employment in the region and there was no need for a protest.

Residents of Shahjahanpur staged a protest at a State Bank of India ATM on Thursday, after the ATM allegedly dispensed a Rs 2,000 note that was a scanned copy of a genuine note and the bank refused to exchange it.

column9: CITU: Centre of Indian Trade Unions
column24: Activists of CITU staged a protest against  the police action as well as government's 'inaction' in the matter of the Shongtong project dispute in Shimla on Thursday.
Surat Congress president Hasmukh Desai and 9 others were arrested for staging a protest and burning the effigy of BJP MLA Praful Pansheria in Varachha locality of Surat city on Thursday.
Miscreants broke into the CPI(M) office at Thokkottu, Ullal, and set banners, posters and furniture on fire. The CPI(M) blamed the Sangh Parivar for the attack.
A poll-related clash between people and the police was reported from Uchahar seat in Rae Bareli district on Thursday during the fourth phase of polling in Uttar Pradesh state.
Shopkeepers staged a protest against the Municipal Corporation of Gurgaon (M CG) clashed over the creation of new hawkers' zone' at the Sector 56 Huda market on Friday evening.

Members of the Brahmin community took out a protest march towards the Mini Secretariat in Kaithal on Friday, to condemn the use of derogatory words against women in a folk song, seeking stern action against the singer.
Members of the Brahmin community staged a protest in Kalayat town, to condemn the use of derogatory words against women in a folk song, seeking stern action against the singer.

Workers under the banner of the Pahaad Khaan Mazdoor Union have been sitting on a dharna in Khanak village for several days, to protest eviction from mining sites despite the Chief Minister’s assurance in this regard.
Clashes broke out between the workers of the Congress and BJP yesterday at Khongjom under Khangabok constituency, where a house of a Congress worker was damaged.

Villagers and cattle smugglers clashed at Kurwali area of Mainpuri district on Friday night in which several people were injured. People seized around 400 cattle from two containers after torching several vehicles. The police controlled the situation.
Right wing groups staged a protest march in Mangalore,  following the BJP protest call against the Kerala CM's participation in a rally for communal harmony.

Hundreds of men and women from two communities (assumed Hindu and Muslim) clashed and pelted stones at each other in a locality of community-sensitive Muzaffarnagar city on Friday night. The violence which left at least six persons injured was caused by the collision of two bikes. The police used mild force to disperse the mob.
Villagers in Neduvasal, Pudukottai district, protested against hydrocarbon exploration and extraction in Tamil Nadu.
Delhi University Teachers Association (DUTA) on Friday staged a protest against the Governing Body of St Stephen's College suggestion to grant more autonomy to educational institutions across India.

Yesterday, a clash broke out due to dispute over expansion of a village road. The incident took place at Padmabil village at Panisagar under North Tripura District after some local people engaged in a clash over the land issue in which 11 people sustained injuries.

Activists of the RSS-affiliated Akhil Bharatiya Vidyarthi Parishad (ABVP) clashed with members of the Left-leaning Students Federation of India (SFI) at the Savitribai Phule Pune University, following a dispute over putting up posters on the Ramjas College controversy. Five students sustained minor injuries in the incident.
A clash took place at Yairipok Bishnunaha under Wangkhem constituency between the workers of the Congress and Lok Jhanshakti Party (LJP) where a Bolero was damaged.

In an encounter with police last night, a top militant leader of the disbanded United A'chik Liberation Army (UALA) Singbirth Marak alias Norrok X Momin was killed, while four to five of them were injured in Meghalaya's North Garo Hills.

Hundreds of villagers, NGO representatives and kin of Ramandeep Kaur (25), who died during delivery at the Abohar Civil Hospital on February 20, staged a protest on the Civil Hospital premises in Abohar on Saturday, against the alleged negligence by the hospital staff which led to her death.
Schoolchildren of the model government school at Baldara village in Baran staged a protest on Saturday, against the decision to repost a popular teacher.
A large number of safai workers staged a protest in Bathinda on Saturday, against the Bathinda police for the ‘delay’ in the arrest of the accused in the murder case of safai worker Jiwan Ram Mamu.
The BJD members sat on a dharna near the Mahatma Gandhi statute protesting against Modi's remark. BJD MLAs, too, stood up and raised slogans against Modi.

Following the student clash at Ramjas College, about 50 ABVP members gathered at the Panjab University's (PU) student centre in Chandigarh on Saturday and raised slogans against All India Students' Association (AISA) and other Left-leaning organisations alleging that the groups have been siding with anti-national elements

Following the student clash at Ramjas College, Students for Society (SFS) organised a protest at the campus of Panjab University in Chandigarh on Saturday, condemning the clash that took place at Ramjas College and slamming ABVP for causing the violence.

Police clashed with and arrested more than 30 BJP leaders and activists when they picketed the residence of district in-charge Minister Vinay Kulkarni in Dharwad, demanding his resignation over his alleged involvement in a party fund case in Karnataka.

Protests erupted in Hyderabad against the shooting in Kansas that killed Hyderabad engineer Srinivas Kuchibhotla. Local leaders criticised US president Donald Trump for instigating hatred among people for political gains.

Several people near Badarwas area of Jaipur city on Saturday surrounded and pelted stones at four trucks, following rumours that these vehicles allegedly transporting cows to slaughter houses. Mansarovar police reached the area to control the angry mob.
One man under Nambol Police station was severely injured today in an election related clash between two rival groups.

A day after a youth succumbed to injuries sustained in an accident, his family and other residents staged a protest and blocked traffic by keeping the body on the road in Ludhiana Saturday. The protesters allegedly pelted stones at policemen and did not allow two ambulances to pass through. The police later resorted to lathicharge to defuse the situation.

Several youth belong to Sikh groups pelted stones at a vehicle from dera followers and started raising slogans against the dera and the administration during a ceremony at Mallanwala block of Ferozepur district on Saturday leading to a clash between the two groups. The police intervened to bring the situation under control.

A Karnataka State Road Transport Corporation bus was stoned and a private lorry was set on fire at separate places in Dakshina Kannada following the BJP protest call against the Kerala CM's participation in a rally for communal harmony.
Villagers and cattle smugglers clashed on the on the Faridnagar -Pilkhua road in Modinagar area of Ghaziabad district on Saturday morning. The police controlled the situation.

Seeking to continue the campaign against the Congress government, BJP workers, led by the former ministers, gathered on New Kantharaja Urs road and tried to march towards the CM's residence in Sharadadevi Nagar, Mysuru. They were not allowed to proceed further by the police, who had blocked the roads leading to the residence. The activists later sat on dharna at the site and raised slogans against the chief minister.

Students of Government Degree College, Nalagarh, took out a protest march at Nalagarh on Saturday against the rape and brutal murder of a 7-year-old girl on Monday. They demanded harsh punishment for the accused.
Villagers in Neduvasal, Pudukottai district, protested against hydrocarbon exploration and extraction in Tamil Nadu for the second day.
About 500 students staged a silent protest against the St Stephen's College authorities' "unilateral" move to seek autonomous status on Saturday in Delhi.

In a huge motorcycle protest rally, the residents went around the city demanding a permanent bench of the OrissaHigh Court here. The protest was organised by Nagarik Kriyanustan Committee and lawyers.

The ongoing protest against the hydrocarbon exploration and extraction in Tamil Nadu intensified on Saturday as a group of students and youths, mobilised through social media, staged a day-long hunger strike in Tiruvarur, opposing the project.

Two gunmen on a motorbike killed a father-son duo, local organisers for the Dera Sacha Sauda, at a congregation centre of the Sirsa-headquartered sect at Jagera village near Malaudh, around 40 km from Khanna in Ludhiana district, on Saturday.  The police suspects Sokh radicals to be behind the attack.

A jawan of the elite CoBRA squad of the CRPF was injured in an encounter with Maoist rebels in Jharkhand's Singhbhum district on Sunday morning. At least five Maoist guerilla fighters also believed to have sustained bullet injuries in the gun battle with the joint forces of paramilitary forces, Jharkhand and West Bengal police in Ghatsila area.

A Cobra jawan of the central paramilitary force was injured and five Maoist guerilla fighters are learnt to have sustained bullet injuries in an encounter between joint forces of Jharkhand and West Bengal and rebels in East Singhbhum district's Ghatsila.
A bomb blast was reported outside the residence of Hueiyen Lanpao (local vernacular) editor H Ningomba and ISTV editor B Ningomba in Okram Chuthek region of Imphal.
Followers of Dera Sacha Sauda held a protest and briefly blocked roads at Mandi Ahmedgarh on Sunday, to protest Saturday’s murder of two dera followers.

column9: AIJASS: All India Jat Aarakshan Sangharsh Samiti
column24: All India Jat Aarakshan Sangharsh Samiti observed a 'Black Day' on Sunday February 26 at its dharna spot at Ballah village in Karnal district during its ongoing agitation for Jat quotas in central government jobs. A group of young protesters disrupted the rail traffic near the protest site. Day 30

A minor clash took place between supporters of the ABVP and the SFS on the Panjab University (PU) campus in Chandigarh on Monday when an SFS member termed supporters of the ABVP at Ramjas College in Delhi “goons”. The police rounded up eight supporters, four each from the ABVP and the SFS, from the university.

column9: AIJASS: All India Jat Aarakshan Sangharsh Samiti
column24: All India Jat Aarakshan Sangharsh Samiti observed a 'Black Day' on Sunday February 26 at its dharna spot at Dadri during its ongoing agitation for Jat quotas in central government jobs. A group of young protesters disrupted the rail traffic near the protest site. Day 30
Around 100 women, mostly residents of Besant Nagar, Chennai, took out a march to express their discontent towards political events that led to the formation of a government under Edappadi K Pala.
Bank employees staged a protest in Valluvarkottam, Chennai, as part of their state-wide strike.

Residents of Hedike village (assumed Herike village in Sangrur district) on Sunday climbed atop a water tank to protest against water shortage in the village after the PSPCL disconnected electric supply to the village waterworks.

Followers of Dera Sacha Sauda held a protest  at Jaghera village, near Khanna, on Sunday, against Saturday’s murder of two dera followers.

column9: AIJASS: All India Jat Aarakshan Sangharsh Samiti
column24: All India Jat Aarakshan Sangharsh Samiti observed a 'Black Day' on Sunday February 26 at its dharna spot at Naraingarh village in Ambala district during its ongoing agitation for Jat quotas in central government jobs. A group of young protesters disrupted the rail traffic near the protest site. Day 30

A large number of students from the neighbouring districts, IT employees from Chennai, and celebrities, visited Neduvasal and sat with the protesters, who were continuing their agitation against hydrocarbon extraction. They argued that the proposed hydrocarbon extraction project would devastate the livelihood of people across the delta region.

Members of the Jawaharlal Nehru University Students Union (JNUSU) lifted their blockade of the administrative building on campus on Sunday where they had been protesting against the May 5 2016 regulations on the new admission process since February 9. Day 18
Hundreds of Kathputli Colony residents gathered at Jantar Mantar in Delhi on Sunday to protest against the delay in their resettlement.
Residents of Nurpur town held a demonstration near the Civil Hospital in Nurpur on Sunday, over the leakage in the septic tank of the hospital.

column24: All India Jat Aarakshan Sangharsh Samiti observed a 'Black Day' on Sunday February 26 at its dharna spot in Palwal district during its ongoing agitation for Jat quotas in central government jobs. A group of young protesters disrupted the rail traffic near the protest site. Day 30
On Sunday, top officers marched to Bihar's Raj Bhawan to 'seek the Governor's intervention to facilitate immediate release of Bihar staff selection commission (BSSC) chairman Sudhir Kumar, IAS.

A group of young protesters disrupted the rail traffic near the protest site. Day 30
The death of the two employees has triggered a massive protest from employees body, Pradhikar Karmchari Sangh, the frontal organization of MADA employees.
Relatives of a murdered financier and locals marched  through the main market of Sangrur city and staged a dharna in front of the Longowal police station on Sunday, to protest police ‘inaction’.

column9: AIJASS: All India Jat Aarakshan Sangharsh Samiti
column24: All India Jat Aarakshan Sangharsh Samiti observed a 'Black Day' on Sunday February 26 at its dharna spot at Sirsa during its ongoing agitation for Jat quotas in central government jobs. A group of young protesters disrupted the rail traffic near the protest site. Day 30

column9: AIJASS: All India Jat Aarakshan Sangharsh Samiti
column24: All India Jat Aarakshan Sangharsh Samiti observed a 'Black Day' on Sunday February 26 at its dharna spot at Umrakheri village near the Panipat-Shamli during its ongoing agitation for Jat quotas in central government jobs. A group of young protesters disrupted the rail traffic near the protest site. Day 30

Hundreds of protesters staged a protest and gheraoed the main hospital complex in Abohar on Monday, against the alleged negligence by the hospital staff which led to the death of a woman during delivery on February 20.

Around 200 students of Gujarat Institute of Nursing Education and Research (GINER) took out a protest rally near the Civil Hospital in Asarwa locality of Ahmedabad city on Monday, seeking suspension of a lecturer following allegations of molestation.
Today, Hindi teachers in Mizoram employed under centrally sponsored scheme began an indefinite hunger strike. They were protesting their terms of employment.
Congress workers staged a protest against privatisation of the electricity supply system of Ajmer at the main gate of Ajmer Vidhyut Vitran Nigam (AVVNL) on Monday.

A poll-related incident of violence was reported from Ayodhya in Faizabad district on Monday during the fifth phase of polling in Uttar Pradesh state. 10 BJP supporters were arrested after they attacked the car of the SP candidate.
Bank employees held a protest against the Union Government in Dehradun on Monday, against the outsourcing of employees to the banking sector.

More than 1,000 asha workers, anganwadi workers, 11-month contract workers and outsourced daily wage labourers, under the banner of Fight for Rights Group, staged a protest in Gandhinagar on Monday, demanding permanent government jobs. When the police detained them one of the protesters tried to jump off the Karai police station roof.

In an incident of poll-related violence a youth damaged an EMV at Abhaipur Belsar booth under the Sadar seat in Gonda district on Monday during the fifth phase of polling in Uttar Pradesh state. He was arrested by the police and the EMV was changed.

A poll-related clash between SP and BJP supporters was reported near Dihrauli booth under Harriya Assembly constituency in Basti district on Monday during the fifth phase of polling in Uttar Pradesh state.

The Hisar police on Monday arrested around 10 students of the Jat community who marched to Matka Chowk in Hisar city on Monday as part of their protest program, demanding to change its name to Jat Saheed Chowk, in memory of Jats killed in the last year's violent quota stir.

The Extra Judicial Execution Victim Family Association Manipur (EEVFAM) today burnt effigies of CM O Ibobi, retd DGP Y Joykumar and CO Ak Jhaljit at Majorkhul Lai Lampak demanding punishment of those involved in the infamous Sanjit fake encounter case.
Kangleipak Students Association (KSA) held a demonstration in front of the Governor's gate today. Later, police came and controlled the agitating students.

Parents and friends of a Class 12th student, who committed suicide at Kavumbaghum after being harassed for taking a selfie with a girl student, organised a dharna at the school and demanded legal action against the school authorities.
Dera Sacha Sauda followers on Monday staged a massive protest in Khanna of Ludhiana district, demanding the arrest of the killers of two of its followers.

Members of the Bar Association, Kharar, on Monday suspended their work and stage a dharna outside the gate of the courts. They were protesting against the decision of the Punjab and Haryana High Court of setting up family courts at the district level and transferring the cases with regard to family matters from sub-divisional courts to district-level courts.
Agitated student leaders staged a gherao band sit-in-demonstration on Monday, alleging high handedness of the authorities and West Bengal Joint Entrance Examination Board.
Residents of Kussa village in Nihalsinghwala sub-division of the Moga district on Monday protested and raised slogans against the local authorities of the power corporation over power disconnection.
An incident of poll-related violence was reported from Lambhua in Sultanpur on Monday during the fifth phase of polling in Uttar Pradesh state.

Followers of Dera Sacha Sauda blocked the road in front of Naam Charcha Ghar of Dera Sacha Sauda in Ludhiana district near Mandi Ahmedgarh, protesting against the authorities’ failure to arrest the killers of two dera followers.

Hundreds more converged on Neduvasal and sat with the protesters, who were continuing their agitation against hydrocarbon extraction. They argued that the proposed hydrocarbon extraction project would devastate the livelihood of people across the delta region.

ABVP students’ union along with Ramjas College students took out a Tiranga march  in North Delhi on Monday, protesting against some Left-leaning students allegedly supporting anti-national activities at Delhi University.
All India Students Association (AISA) staged a protest against the violent clash at Ramjas College in Delhi on Monday.

column9: NSUI: National Students' Union of India
column24: Congress’ National Students Union of India (NSUI) staged a protest against the violent clash at Ramjas College in Delhi on Monday.

Rashtrawadi Shikshak Sangh, an RSS-affiliated teachers’ faction, staged a silent protest at the varsity’s Arts Faculty of Delhi University on Monday, demanding “check on abuse of freedom of speech and expression by the Left-groups”.
Dozens of teachers gheraoed the office of the District Education Officer, Patiala, to protest against his alleged misbehaviour with teachers.
The Bihar Police Service Association (BPSA) on Monday held a meeting protesting the suspension of Sonepur sub-divisional police officer Mohammed Ali Ansari.

Hundreds of students on Monday staged a protest outside the Jharkhand Public Service Commission (JPSC) head office in Ranchi. They were alleging anomalies in the evaluation of the papers in prelims test of JPSC .

Today, a group of people torched the vehicle of a flying squad team on election duty at Khundrakpam assembly constituency, Imphal East district. The incident took place at Sambei under Sagolmang police station, after a polling booth of Congress party was dismantled near Khundrakpam Laiharaoba Lampak by a rival group.
Police detained a few bank employees for holding a protest opposite Union Bank's branch in Nanpura locality of Surat city on Monday.
An incident of poll-related violence was reported from Tarabganj constituencies in Gonda district on Monday during the fifth phase of polling in Uttar Pradesh state.

ABVP and a rival students group which had recently parted ways with Congress-backed National Students Union of India (NSUI) clashed on the campus of Maharaja Sayajirao University of Baroda (MSU) in Vadodara on Monday. The crowd dispersed only after police reached the spot to bring the situation under control.
Naxalites allegedly set ablaze a forest timber depot and blocked a road with logs in Sironcha tehsil, Gadchiroli district of Maharashtra.

In an incident of poll-related violence, supporters of one local candidate attacked villagers who had voted for another candidate at Mattu Ka Purwa village under Raniganj constituency in Pratapgarh district on Monday during the fifth phase of polling in Uttar Pradesh state. The accused chopped off the nose of a woman and thrashed her husband and children. The injured were admitted to the district hospital.
Four people sustained serious injuries while one had to be admitted to Gomati district hospital in Udaipur, as BSF jawans opened fire allegedly on a group of ostensibly innocent people.

Over 2,000 students of Guru Nanak Girls College on Tuesday staged a protest and blocked the chowk outside the college at Model Town in Ludhiana city, after the names of 50 students were struck off due to attendance shortage.
ABVP members  staged a counter protest against the massive demonstration by left-leaning student groups and teachers outside DUSU office on Tuesday.

column9: NSUI: National Students' Union of India

column23: Daily Pakistan Today; The Balochistan Times (AsiaNet)
column24: 5 people were injured in a roadside explosion in the Arang tehsil of Bajaur Agency. One of those injured later died.
Iranian forces fired four mortar shells across the border into Panjgur district. No injuries reported.
A bomb blast was reported in Upper Kurram district. It hit a loaded trailer entering pakistan from Afghanistan, but caused no injuries.
A protest demonstration was recorded by the eunuchs of Bhan Syedabad against the arrest of their community leaders.
Farmers in the Siyal Mines area protested against shortages of water.

The candidates applying for the recruitments in Sindh Police Hyderabad district including Mohammad Abrejo, Ghulam Razam, Abdul Razaq, Mohammad Ismail and others recorded a protest demonstration against the corruption in the appointment of the police constables.
People protested and blocked roads outside government departments in Shahdara and Iqbal town.
Students from various educational institutions in Khyber Agency protested at Bab-e-Khyber in Jamrud against the suspension of their educational scholarships.
Students staged a protest on University Road to protest over students killed in road accidents recently.
Family members of a man they believe was murdered by police staged a protest at Hilal-e-Ahmar Chowk to demand action against the suspects.

Scores of protesters from the opposition PPP and PML-N and six independent members of the district council staged a demonstration in front of the deputy commissioner's office against the sealing of the district nazim's office.

Teachers of the Government Dini Madarsa High School protested against a transfer of some of their colleagues.
The members of the Municipal Employees' Union staged a protest demonstration in Larkana for the issuance of their withheld salaries.

A large number of farmers protested in front of Haseeb Waqas Sugar Mills in the Nankana Sahib area and blocked the Head Punjnad road to draw attention to their grievances.

A large number of citizens protested on Fawara Chowk near the Faiz-ul-Islam Mosque over its sale to a private owner.
People protested and blocked roads outside government departments in Shahdara and Iqbal town.

Different protest demonstrations were recorded in Tando Muhammad Khan by the activists of Sindh Peoples' Youth, PPP, Peoples' Labor Bureau and other organizations for arrest of the Sabir Bhutto's murderers.
Around 40 students associated with an MQM faction's student wing involved in a clash with another MQM faction's student wing were arrested in the Gulshan area.
14 militants from Afghanistan were killed in an attack the Olai border checkpost in the Baizai area of Mohmand Agency. One FC member was injured.
2 FC personnel were injured by unidentified assailants in the Balgather area of Turbat.
After a robbery in Bhan Saeedabad some traders protested over the icnident and demanded action.
The residents of different areas of Bhan Syedabad recorded a protest demonstration against the poor sanitary conditions.
Traders of Chakesar tehsil observed a shutter down strike against the assistant commissioner for imposing 'unjust and heavy' fines on them. The traders also staged a demonstration.
Farmers of Pahore Branch, Chinjani Branch and Pithoro Branch protested against a shortage of water.
The lower staff employees of the Education Department in Dadu recorded a protest demonstration in favor of their demands.
A protest against police was held as thieves stole gold ornaments, cash, prize bonds and other valuables worth Rs3.3 million from the house of a trader in Daska city's Muhallah Wahab Masjid locality.
The residents of Qasimabad and Latifabad recorded a protest demonstration against the acute shortage of drinking water outside the Hyderabad press club.
The sanitation staff of the Municipal Corporation staged a sit-in at Fawara Chowk for hours to press for the acceptance of their demand.

The residents of Faizabad Colony led by Attaullah Rajput, Naeem Ahmed Pathan, Ibrahim, Jood, Sarfraz Burdi and others staged a protest demonstration outside the SEPCO office Khairpur against unannounced and excessive load shedding.
At least 4 people were injured in a grenade attack by two men on a motorcycle in the Lyari area of Karachi.

Members of the Progressive Students Alliance of the Punjab University staged a protest demonstration outside the Lahore Press Club (LPC) against the alleged violence on campus by a student organisation.

PEDM members staged a protest inside PU's Hostel Number 4, demanding protection from the IJT 'goons'. They alleged the varsity administration was protecting the IJT activists and no action had been taken against hooliganism.
3 FC personnel were killed by a roadsibe bomb in the Toi Khulla area of South Waziristan. The TTP claimed responsibility.
5 security personnel were injured as they were attempting to defuse a bomb in the Damadola locality of Mamond tehsil of Bajaur Agency. No group claimed responsibility.
The relatives of martyred journalist Azeem Laghari, who was killed in 2008 staged a protest demonstration for the provision of job to the brother of deceased in Dadu.
People blocked the Karakoram Highway to protest the proposed inclusion of Pales area into the Upper Kohistan district.

Activists of Pakistan Peoples Party-Shaheed Bhutto launched 'insaf march' from Jacobabad, which reached Larkana press club the same day, to protest against government failure to serve justice in the 20-year-old murder case of Mir Murtaza Bhutto and his companions.
The citizens of Pangrio staged protest demonstration against the low gas pressure in Jacobabad.

The members of the Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaaf Johi chapter led by Abdul Majeed Laghari, Rashid Lund and others staged a protest demonstration outside the Johi press club against torture of their Johi chapter President Pir Bux Chandio by SHO Aslam Bughio.
50 students led by some leaders of student groups marched from Kotri to Karachi to demand the revival of student unions in Pakistan.

Hundreds of auto-drivers riding on three-wheelers took out a protest rally from Lorry Adda to Lahore railways station to condemn the so-called taxes and fine tickets issued by the Lahore transport company.
A police mobile van was attacked with a cracker blast near Five Star Chowrangi in the Nazimabad area of Karachi. No casualties reported.
Hundreds of PPP workers took out a protest rally outside the Okara press club against the recent attack against PPP leader Shaukat Basra.
Sukkur residents protested against an encroachment drive which was allegedly started without adequate notice.
A leader of the transgender community in Lahore was killed in her house. This caused protests the next day.
An assistant camera person working with Samaa TV was killed near Karachi's KDA Chowrangi. The TTP claimed responsibility for the attack.
At least 2 police officers were killed and 12 injured in an explosion while they were trying to defuse a bomb at Sariab Road near the Karachi Bus Terminal in Quetta.
3 people were injured in a landmine blast as they were driving a water tanker in Dera Bugti town.
Nurses at Civi Hospital Bolan went on strike and staged a protest to demand attention to their grievances.

The activists of Jamaat-i-Islami's youth wing locked the emergency unit of district headquarters hospital and staged a demonstration at the Farooq Azam Chowk in Charsadda to register their protest against the transfer of four doctors from the health facility.
A protest demonstration was recorded by the activists of the PTI Dadu against the SHO of Dadu Police.
The family members of a journalist namely Azeem Laghari, who was killed in an armed men attack nine years ago, recorded a protest demonstration for the arrest of his murderers.
Residents of Mohmand Agency protested at Ghalanai to demand an immediate merger of FATA and KPK. Various groups and political parties supported the protest.
The tail-end growers of the Siyal Mines continued their protest demonstration for the de-silting work of the Siyal Mines in the Hingorja area.
The PML-F activists and the Dahri community people continued their protest demonstration for the recovery of a missing youth leader Fayaz Dahri in the Hingorja area.
People from all walks of life gathered outside the National Press Club to observe the Women's Day.
The employees union of Tehsil Municipal Administration Karak staged a rally and locked their offices in protest against the non-payment of salaries to them.
Transgender persons protested the killing of one of their community members, Muskaan by holding a demonstration on Mall Road.

The Druggists, Chemists and Pharmaceutical Manufacturers Associations observed complete strike in the city and closed all the medical stories to protest the amendments in Drug Act 1976 by Punjab government.
They also took out protest rallies on Murree Road and Mall Road triggering massive traffic jam creating problems for vehicular movement and pedestrians.
Pharmacists, chemists and owners of therapeutic goods stores protested outside the Lahore Press Club against proposed amendments to the Drug Act.
The local journalists of Mirpurkhas recorded a protest demonstration against the murder of a cameraman of a private news channel in Karachi in an armed attack.

After police attacked a school and abused the prinicpal over a law and order incident there, schoolteachers and the students recorded a protest demonstration against the police officer responsible and demanded of the IGP Sindh AD Khuwaja to take notice of the matter, otherwise they have threatened to extend their protest circle.
Farmers continued their sit-in and protest camp outside the main gate of the Haseeb Waqas Sugar Mills for the third day to stop the sugar movement outside the mill and demanded payment of their dues.
Two rival student groups (PTI and PEDM) protested at Punjab University related to their recent class on campus.
Traders belonging to pharmaceutical business held a protest rally here at Rawalpindi Press Club against what they called amendments in the draft of Drug Act 1976 and Drug regulatory Act 2012.
The local students of Thari Mirwah recorded a protest demonstration against the administration of the Government Law College Khairpur for not providing admissions to them in session 2017.

At least 13 people were killed, including 2 police, and over 100 wounded in a suicide bombing in front of the Punjab Assembly building. The attack was claimed by Jamaat-ur-Ahrar, a faction of the TTP. The suicide bombing took place during a protest by pharmacists. The police who were killed were protecting the protest. At least one person later died of their injuries.
Three members of a local jirga were killed and another was injured when a vehicle they were travelling in came under fire by unidentified assailants in Sheikhan village of central Orakzai Agency.
Residents of different areas of Bhan Saeedabad protested against poor sanitation conditions in their area.
Nurses of the Civil Hospital and Bolan Medical College Hospital continued their protest to demand the government accept their demands.
Rawalpindi and Islamabad journalists protested outside the National Press Club over the perceived targeting of journalists in terror attacks.
People of Andaki and adjoining localities in the Karak area protested against vacant teachers posts in the area.
Following the death of a boy in hospital his relatives attacked the staff of the hospital and broke windowpanes. The family protested and alleged that the doctor's negligence led to the boy's death.
Hospital patients and attendants set up two protest camps in Rawalpindi over the closure of medical stores and problems getting medicines related to the pharmacist strikes.
At least 6 people were killed, including 4 FC personnel, 2 civilians and the bomber, in a suicide attack by suspected TTP militants in the Sheikh banda suburb of Ghalanai.

Following a suicide bombing in Ghalanai, FC personnel killed 5 suspected TTP militants in the Ghalanai area. Another suicide attack in Mohmand Agency was also reported, kiling 2 people (including the bomber).
An intelligence agency member was injured by unidentified assailants in the Nasirabad area near his home.
6 Jamaat ul Ahrar militants were killed in an encounter with police in Khanewal district.
Family members of a murdered youth protested to demand the police find the culprits.
Doctors and paramedics of the women and children's hospital of Bannu boycotted their duties and protests over alleged hooliganism of the attendants of a patient at the facility.
Farmers in the Siyal Mines area protested against shortages of water and to demand de-silting in their area.
Family members of some missing people protested in Kandiaro against local officials for delays in recovering their bodies after a boat capsized on the Indus River.
PPP-SB activists continued their protest outside the Session Court in Khairpur against alleged corruption in development works in the area.
Members of the Buriro community protested against an attack on their homesby members of the Phulpoto community and demanded police take action.
Journalists, political party activists and civil society members protested in Landi Kotal against threats and absuive language used against some reporters of Geo News.
Residents of Siddiqui colony in Larkana protested against the SEPCO authorities for disconnecting their power supplies.
Local journalists in Mehar protested against the murder of a cameraman in Karachi.
Members of the WAPDA Hydroelectric Labor Union in Moro continued their protest against the actions and alleged corruption of the organization's executive engineer.
Farmers blocked the road between Rahim Yar Khan and Khanpur to demand the restoration of sugarcane crushing at Chaundhry Sugar Mills Kot Samaba.
Hospital patients and attendants continued their protest in Rawalpindi over the closure of medical stores and problems getting medicines related to the pharmacist strikes.
PTI activists and other civil society members protested outside the Rawalpdini press club over the continued strike of chemists and pharmacists.
The Sindh Professors and Lecturerers Association protested and staged a sit-in at the Karachi press club to demand the implementation of a four-tier promotion formula.
Christian community members in Sialkot protested to demand police find the killers of a Christian youth.
Lawyers in Sukkur protested over recent terrorist attacks targeting lawyers and demanded the government offer better protection.

A suicide bomber hit a vehicle of the judiciary near the Hayatabad Medical Complex Peshawar, killing the vehicles driver and seriously wounding at least 12 others, including 3 female civil judges. The TTP claimed responsibility.
18 suspected militants, includng at least 5 LeJ members, were killed by Pakistan Rangers personnel in the Mangohpir area of Karachi.
At least 11 suspected militants were killed during operations in KPK following the Sehwan shrine bombing (4 fatalities coded in another event).
3 soldiers were killed and 2 wounded by an IED in Balochistan's Awaran district.
Family members of some slain men were protested against their killing and blocked the Khichian-Barnala Road to demand the arrest of the killers.
Lower stff employees of the Education Department in Dadu protested in favour of their demands.
Family members of a missing youth PML-F leader, Fayaz Dahri, protested in Hingorja to demand his recovery.
Farmers of the Siyal Mines area protested to demand de-silting in their area.
JUI-F activists protested and staged a sit-in in Jacobabad against corruption.
After a student was hit by a bus and killed, students of Sindh University in the Jamshoro area protested against the university administration.
JI organized a protest at Kandi Kotal bazaar against alleged delaying tactics of abolishing the Frontier Crimes Regulation (FCR) and implementation of promised reforms.
Members of a disabled persons organization protested at the Larkana press club to demand provision of rights for them.
Members of the municipal employees union staged a protest to demand the issuance of withheld salaries.
Residents of Siddiqui colony in Larkana continued their protest against the SEPCO authorities for disconnecting their power supplies.

Prosecutors, attorneys and other staff of the public prosecutor and district attorney from Thatta and Sujawal districts protested and march to the Makli Press Club to demand perks. They also staged a sit-in.
A protest rally was staged by APCA members in Mirpurkhas against a local PPP leader.
Hundreds of MWM activists protested at the Burhan Wani Shaheed Chowk near the Central Press Club in Muzaffarabad.
PPP activists protested in Tando Bago against the alleged high-handedness ofofficials taking part in an anti-encroachment drive in the area.

column8: Government of the Islamic Republic of Pakistan
column24: Pakistan closed the Torkham border crossing following the Sehwan shrine bombing. Shortly after Pakistan also shut the Chaman border crossing in Balochistan.

At least 72 people were killed and as many as 270 injured by a suspected TTP suicide bombing at the Lal Shahbaz Qalandar shrine in Sehwan. Daesh claimed responsibility for the attack. 18 others died later of their injuries.
4 suspected TTP militants were killed in a clash with security forces in the Kakakhel area of Bannu.
2 soldiers and 6 suspected TTP militants were killed during an attack on two checkposts in Orakzai Agency.
4 police officers and one other person was killed, in attack on their vehicle in Dera Town.
2 FC personnel were injured by unidentified assailants who attacked across the Af-Pak border in Khyber Agency. One assailants was killed in retaliatory fire.
2 suspected militants were killed in the Sargodha area by CTD police.
2 suspected TTP militants were killed in Lower Kurram by Levies Force personnel.
4 suspected TTP militant commanders were killed during an operation in the Mumazo area of Orakzai Agency.
2 suspected TTP militants were killed by security forces in the Tora Warai area.
At least 100 suspected militants were killed in operations in the 24 hours following the Sehwan shrine bombing (58 fatalities coded in other events).
7 suspected militants were killed in the Kathore area by Pakistan Rangers forces during operations following the Sehwan shrine bombing.
At least one militant belonging to a banned group was killed in an ecounter with police near Darakshan Scheme in Quetta.

column23: The Express Tribune; The Frontier Post; Daily Regional Times
column24: The Pakistan military claims to have destroyed 12 TTP camps, including those run by the Jamaat ul Ahrar group, in Afghanistan in the areas opposite Mohmand and Khyber Agencies over 2 days. As many as 37 militants were also reported killed, including a senior trainer of suicide bombers.
6 suspected TTP militants were killed and 10 hideouts destroyed in airstrikes in Khyber Agency.

Activists of different organizations protested in Larkana over the Sehwan shrine bombing.
Residents of Mir Ali Bazaar staged a demo against SPECO authorities for long periods of load shedding.
Employees of STEVTA protested in favour of their demands in Mirpurkhas.
Scores of people protested in Peshawar at the local press club against the Sehwan shrine bombing.
Tribal students of various educational institutions protested outside the Peshawar press club against delays in the merger between KPK and FATA.
Activists of the MWM protested against the Sehwan shrine bombing at Ranipur.

Police used aerial firing to disperse mourners in Sehwan who were protesting over the recent suicide attack there. The mourners set fire to a police van after officials denied them entry to the shrine that was targeted. At least 10 were injured in clashes with police.
Activists of different parties, including MWM, JUI and Sunni Tehreek, protested in Sujawal against the Sehwan shrine bombing.
The business community protested in Tando Muhammad Khan and surrounding areas, including Shaikh Bharkio and Mullah Katyar, over the Sehwan shrine bombing.
The business community protested in Tando Muhammad Khan and surrounding areas, including Shaikh Bharkio and Mullah Katyar, over the Sehwan shrine bombing.
Police arrested 35 Afghan nationals for illegally residing in the Rangpura locality of Sialkot.
3 suspected militants were killed in a gunfight with security forces in Dera Ismail Khan.

Police baton-charged and fired tear gas at a group of protesters in the Bhimber area, injuring 4, as they tried to intercept the convoy of the AJK PM.
Unidentified assailants threw a grenade at the house of a Union Council Nazim in the Totalai neighbourhood of Buner. It caused some damage to the house.
Lower stff employees of the Education Department in Dadu protested in favour of their demands.
Activists from different groups including the MWM, JUI and Sunni Tehreek protested in Dadu against the Sehwan srhine bombing.
After 2 people were killed during a court appearance, the families protested against insecurity.

Family members of a missing youth PML-F leader, Fayaz Dahri, protested in Hingorja to demand his recovery.
MWM activists protested in Hingorja against the recent Sehwan shrine bombing.
Residents of Kandhkot protested against suspensions of gas supplies.
Members of a Kohat-based NGO protested at the local press club over the killing of a female member of their organization in the Ustarzai area recently.
Activists of the JUI Larkana district and Humanism Organization Pakistan protested against the Sehwan shrine bombing.
Civil society activists staged a demo outside the Karachi press club against the Sehwan shrine bombing.
Protest rallies and a strike were held in Setharja by its business community to protest over the Sehwan shrine bombing.
Punjab police and other LEA personnel arrested at least 92 people in an ongoing crackdown following the Sehwan shrine bombing.
30 people, including 10 Afghans, were arrested in the Pattoki area as part of a larger crackdown following the Sehwan shrine bombing.
5 Jamaat ul Ahrar members were killed by CTD police in the Turko Adda area of Coubara tehsil.

At least 11 TTP militants, including 2 commanders, were killed in an anti-terror offensive in Kurram Agency by the security forces. 11 of those killed were foreigners, while at least 4 were injured. The militants were allegedly trying to enter Pakistan and were stopped in the Superkot and Para Chamkani areas.
7 suspected militants were killed in an encounter with Pakistan Rangers personnel in Shah Latif town of Karachi. One Ranger was injured.

Pakistani fighter jets bombed suspected TTP bases in the Wuchi Bibi area of NWA and the Rena Parchao area of Khyber Agency. The military said hideouts had been destroyed and militants killed, with later reports putting the number at at least 17.
